title: easy, cheesy green bean pasta
directions: Drain green beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine green beans and reserved liquid with remaining ingredients; heat through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Sift dry ingredients and alternately add with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake until lightly brown on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add crackers or dried cereal until meat loaf sticks together.
Then form mini meat loaves.
Put around edge of casserole dish.
Fill rest of dish with peeled potato quarters. Add butter.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soups (except dry soup mix), milk and rice together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and dot with 4 teaspoons butter.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours at 250°.
Don't peek!!!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until set.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Generously grease 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Cook ground beef with onion; drain well. Stir mixture of soup, water and milk in a bowl, then add cooked beef, onions and baking mix. Stir until fully mixed. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add mashed bananas and unbeaten eggs.
Mix flour, soda and nuts together and add to above.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: buddy bars
directions: In a large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: western beef and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut olives into large pieces.
Brown the ground beef in the oil; remove the meat from the pan.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and rice.
Cook, stirring, until browned.
Add the tomatoes, water, seasonings, meat and olives; bring to a boil. Pour into a 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with milk.
Spread on 10 1/2-inch diameter platter.
Chop green pepper.

title: egg sauce
directions: Combine.
Serve as a condiment.
Good over green beans, peas and lima beans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend margarine with spoon until creamy.
Slowly add sugar continuing to work until light.
Slowly stir in white corn syrup and maple syrup.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
Fold in 2 cups pecans.
Pour into chilled unbaked (9-inch) pie shell.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: meat casserole
directions: Lightly brown meat, onions and celery.
Add the rest of the ingredients and put into casserole.
Cover and bake in 325° oven 1 hour, stirring several times.

title: fruit dip
directions: Garnish with chopped nuts and serve with fruit or your favorite munchies.
To make this a low-fat dip, use fat-free cream cheese, fat-free sour cream and instead of the Cool Whip, use Dream Whip, which has to be prepared first.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple strawberry cheese delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: sunday chicken
directions: All soups should be undiluted.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Mix pudding with skim milk.
Add to pudding mix 1/2 of Cool Whip or sugar-free topping.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Use 1/2 of remaining Cool Whip to cover chocolate pudding mixture.
Repeat, using the rest of the chocolate pudding and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 8 even pieces when completely chilled.
One piece equals 1 milk, 1 bread and 1 fat.

title: taco mac and cheese
directions: Brown meat in large skillet and drain. Stir in 2 3/4 cups water, salsa and chili powder. Bring to boil; stir in macaroni. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until water is almost absorbed. Add cheese and stir until melted. Top with crushed tortilla chips. (Green onions and tomatoes, chopped, are optional.)

title: cup-o-dirt dessert
directions: You will also need eight 7-ounce clear plastic cups.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions or use leftover rice.
When cooled, mix in Miracle Whip, hard-boiled eggs, cut up radishes and cucumber.
With the cucumber, I peel it, slice it longways and take out seeds, then cut up; looks like celery. This is so easy to make and it is a good substitute for potato salad.
We love it. It is great in the summer with chicken, cold cuts, hot dogs, hamburgers, etc.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Break cake in small
pieces.
Mix
of
cake pieces with the dry strawberry jello;
put

bottom of a tube cake pan. Spread strawberries over cake pieces, then spread 1/3 of softened ice cream over
strawberries.

Next, spread drained blueberries over lime cake layer, then 1/3
of ice cream.
Mix orange jello and remaining cake;
put in
pan.
Spread orange pieces over cake, then spread the last third of ice cream over oranges.
Freeze. To serve, remove from

and
slice in wedges.
Very pretty and tasty dessert.

title: pork chop and rice bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper chops.
Brown them in a little butter.
In a bowl, mix soup.
Using empty can to measure, add in 1 can milk, 1 can of rice and add the drippings from the chops.
Put chops in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over chops. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Most good!

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Melt margarine or butter with water and oil in saucepan over medium-high heat; bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup buttermilk, baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Pour into an 18 x 11-inch rectangular roasting pan.
Bake until tester inserted in center of cake comes out clean, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add bananas. Sift dry ingredients. Mix with pecans. Add to first mixture. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan or Bundt pan for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool, debone and cut up.
Drain mixed vegetables and pour in bowl.
Mix soups, broth and chicken. Place one shell in bottom of large bake proof pie dish.
Spread out.
Pour mix in shell.
Put other pie shell upside-down over mixture.
Seal edges.
Cut 3 slices in top of pie.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix and let stand 48 hours.

title: grandma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked potato skins(low-fat)
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 35 minutes.
Slice lengthwise and scoop out potato.
Save potato for another dish.
Cut skins into quarters; fill with mushrooms and sliced onion.
Put cheese on top. Bake in a 250° oven until cheese is melted.

title: skillet candy
directions: Heat skillet.
Melt butter; add dates, sugar and eggs.
Mix eggs in good.
(Beat.)
Stir all the time until forms ball like fudge.
Stir in Krispies and nuts; shape in four rolls.
Then roll in coconut and wrap in foil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In
greased casserole dish (9 x 6-inch), spread 2/3 cup stuffing,
then
add cooked chicken evenly over stuffing.
Mix mushroom soup and broth together and spread over chicken.
Mix together
cup	hot
water and 2 tablespoons melted butter with
1 1/3 cups stuffing until moistened.	Spread over casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Will be bubbly.

title: red, white and blueberry delight
directions: In a large bowl, combine condensed milk, lemon juice and lemon peel; mix well.
Stir in yogurt, marshmallows and nuts.

title: roast on the run
directions: In a large crock-pot (slow cooker), combine all ingredients; salt and pepper roast to taste.
Bouillon cubes will flavor and salt water for everything to "slow cook" in.
Cook on "hi" for 4 to 6 hours or "low" all day.

title: easy egg casserole
directions: Brown and partially drain sausage.
Saute onion and mushrooms in remaining fat; drain.
Remove crusts from bread; butter slices and arrange one layer, buttered side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with ham or bacon and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Add another layer of buttered bread and top with sausage, mushrooms and onions.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over layers in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli big dish
directions: Mix rice, onion and broccoli in 3-quart casserole dish.
In separate bowl, heat on stove the remaining ingredients.
Pour over top ingredients and bake for 45 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine milk, butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Beat frosting until spreading consistency. Spread frosting on top of 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: bachelor's company casserole
directions: Saute onions in vegetable oil, also green pepper until tender. Add ground beef and brown well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake covered in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with root vegetables
directions: Marinate chicken in wine, lemon juice, garlic, olive oil and thyme for at least 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix in large bowl by hand.
A little water may be added to help mix.
Roll into small balls and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
These may be made in advance to freeze or placed in refrigerator until time for cooking.

title: aunt dot's refreshing noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles in 1 quart water with 1 tsp salt.
Drain and let stand in large bowl.

title: veggie pizza (low-fat)
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo and dressing with mixer until smooth. Cut bread into fourths and spread mix on it.
Top with veggies and cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together the peanut butter and margarine.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until combined.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on wax paper.
Let stand until dry (about 20 minutes).

title: oven chicken fricassee
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt, pepper, thyme and garlic salt in a bag.
Add chicken and shake.
Lay side by side in greased shallow pan.
Sprinkle with onion flakes, then spread with soup (no water).
Sprinkle parsley flakes over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake an hour at 325°; uncover to crisp at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together egg, shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and water in which soda is dissolved.
Sift together 3 cups flour and spices.
Add to liquid mixture.
Add enough flour to handle (about 3 more cups).
Roll out on floured board at about 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.

title: super easy meatballs
directions: Thaw meatballs in refrigerator overnight. Place meatballs, jelly and chili sauce in crock-pot. Heat on high for 1 hour or until sauce is smooth and meatballs are heated through.

title: tea biscuit
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Cut in shortening with fork until mealy. Add beaten egg to milk. Add carefully to other ingredients. Toss on slightly floured board or paper. Roll 1/4-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter. Spread 1 biscuit with soft butter. Place a second biscuit on top. Place in a slightly floured pan and bake in a moderate oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and sausage and drain.
Add garlic, basil, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water. Drain and rinse in cold water.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake following directions on box in a sheet pan. Allow cake to cool, then cut in half. Crumble one of the cake halves in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix together pineapple, pecans and cherry pie filling.
Layer half of the mixture on cake crumbs. Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Pour half over fruit mixture. Crumble other half of cake on top of cake and sprinkle with nuts or coconut, if desired.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Continue to boil until desired thickness is reached.
Serve over hot, buttered biscuits. This is a perfect breakfast on a cold winter morning.
It can also be boiled until very thick and used as a topping for ice cream.

title: carol's one dish casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix oil and sugar; add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and soda and add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts, apples and raisins.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bob's calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and set aside.
Cut bacon into 1 1/2-inch pieces; brown well and set aside.
Brown onion in small amount of bacon fat.
Mix together salt, dry mustard, vinegar and ketchup.
Place everything in a crock-pot or slow cooker and heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Excellent for barbecue or for dipping tortilla chips.

title: scallops with linguine and vegetables
directions: In saucepan bring salted water to boil.
Cook linguine according to package directions, adding vegetables during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain. Keep warm.

title: butterfly flank steak
directions: Slice flank steak diagonally into thin strips.
(Slice sirloin into 1/4-inch slices.)
Mix remaining ingredients, except flour and oil.
Soak meat for 10 minutes in sauce.
Coat with flour. Deep fry.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Put 1/4 cup in mug; add hot water.

title: corque monsieur
directions: Dip bread in melted butter and brown on both sides on griddle. Cover 2 slices with ham.
Top with second slice bread.
Melt cheese with wine over hot water.
Cover the sandwiches with the cheese mixture.
Serve.

title: ann lovelace punch(party punch)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Divide in thirds and freeze.
When ready to use, set out of freezer long enough to make
slush.
Use 2 bottles of ginger ale to each third of slush. Each third of slush is enough for about 40 people.

title: raspberry swirl cheesecake pie
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 5 minutes longer. Remove from oven. Reduce heat to 350°.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for about 2 hours before serving.

title: marshmallow surprise salad
directions: Cut marshmallows into fourths with wet scissors.
In large bowl combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly but lightly.
Chill. Makes 6 servings.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream the butter and shortening until very light.
Add brown sugar gradually, creaming all until fluffy.
Add white sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a well-greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.

title: amber pickles
directions: Peel and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Try with toothpick.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Make syrup with sugar, vinegar and spices. Bring to boil.
Pour over drained cucumbers.
Let stand overnight. Drain syrup off and bring to boil.
Pour over again and let stand.
Next day, boil all together.
Add cherries, cut in pieces. Seal in hot, sterile jars.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all with Miracle Whip (enough to mix together).

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes.
Place in casserole dish; cover with sugar and salt.
Sprinkle spice over sugar.
Cover with pats of butter.
Twist slice of lemon and place peel in with potatoes. Sprinkle flour over potatoes.
Add water to mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Baste potatoes frequently with syrup.

title: prune relish
directions: Soak prunes in enough wine to cover.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Soak overnight.
Serve with cold ham or other cold cuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix flour, meal, onion and cheese. Next, add eggs, butter and broccoli; mix well. Pour into a greased pan and bake until golden brown, for about 30 minutes (I use an iron skillet). Check it and enjoy.

title: cookies
directions: Cut cookie roll in 9 pieces, then in 1/4.
Bake in a small cookie pan at 400° for 8 minutes.
Bring out of oven and put a small Reese's peanut butter cup in each cookie.
Cool and take out of pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and cut up.
Mix sour cream, mayo, and milk. Stir in rest of ingredients serve with your favorite chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir into corn the flour, salt, sugar and butter.
Beat the eggs well.
Put in half and half and milk.
Stir into corn and put into pan or Pyrex, greased well.
Bake 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven.
Stir from bottom 3 times while baking.

title: mock english toffee
directions: Line jelly roll pan with wax paper.
Arrange crackers, salt side down, in pan.
Boil margarine and brown sugar together for 5 minutes.
Spread over crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 400°. Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Melt and spread; sprinkle with nuts.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into finger strips and place in single layer over fruit.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter. Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: oyster chicken
directions: Rub inside and outside of chickens with salt.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Rub outside of chickens with 1/4 cup oyster sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 400°.
This results in an ono crispy-skinned chicken.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir until meat and onion are tender. Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly. Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: crescent roll dessert
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 pkg. rolls.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Pour over rolls.
Layer with 1 pkg. rolls.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Mix powered sugar with a little milk to make glaze, and drizzle on top.

title: sausage and apple cream cheese puffs
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook sausage to gray stage. Add apple and stir-fry until apple is tender and sausage is lightly brown. Drain off fat and liquid. Season with salt and pepper. Place sausage and apple in a mixing bowl; add cream cheese and blend well.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix and heat until margarine melts.
Remove; add 2 well-beaten eggs and 1 cup sugar; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, leave in pan and cover with miniature marshmallows while still warm.
When cool, frost.

title: strawberry jell-o pie
directions: Place the strawberries in the bottom of the pie shell.
Combine in a saucepan 1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and pinch of salt. Add 1 cup boiling water and boil 1-3 minutes until mixture thickens.
Add 3 tablespoons strawberry jell-o (right from box) and 2 tablespoons white Karo syrup.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix next 3 ingredients in another bowl; set aside.
Place cooked spinach in bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture over spinach.
Layer uncooked noodles.
Pour tomato mixture over noodles.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili soup
directions: Saute onion in oil in large pot over medium heat until tender but not browned, about 6 minutes.
Add garlic, chili powder and oregano; cook 30 seconds.
Add vegetables, broth, stewed tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Wash kale; cut stalks into small pieces. Coarsely chop leaves.
Add to soup with rice.
Cover and cook gently 20 minutes or until stalks are tender.
Add beans.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Put warm water in bowl.
Dissolve yeast.
Add margarine, sugar and flour.
Stir well.
Drop tablespoon in greased muffin tins. May use part and keep other part in refrigerator up to one week. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice sugar cookie roll into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on floured and greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Punch with a fork to keep it flat.
Cool completely.

title: simple brown sugar bar
directions: Mix oil, sugar and egg. Stir in other ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with butter, 1/4 cup milk and nuts.
Put 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Melt the caramels and 1/4 cup milk.
Place chips on cake.
Pour caramel on top. Drop rest of batter on top. Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: You will need sandwich picks (wood).

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together the sugar, oil, eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves, then add the chopped walnuts.
Add the flour mixture to the zucchini mixture and stir well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour + a few minutes, or until bread tests done.

title: hearty hot dog casserole
directions: Slice hot dogs into 1-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 can of onions and cheese in ungreased round 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover and bake until potatoes are tender 45 to 50 minutes.
Arrange onions around casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, margarine and eggs in a mixing bowl. Add milk, flour, salt and flavorings. Mix well. Pour into a greased tube pan. Place in a cold oven. Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in water, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips.

title: chicken delight
directions: Fix flour seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic salt (enough to coat chicken).
Shake chicken to coat.
Heat oil and butter in skillet and brown chicken. Drain oranges and reserve juice.
Mix juices, honey, soy sauce and ginger.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and simmer 30 minutes until done. When chicken is fork-tender, add oranges and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water; drain.
Sprinkle salt in skillet and cook meat until slightly brown.
Stir spaghetti sauce into meat.
Add oregano and Italian seasoning to taste.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine sugar, milk, oil and eggs until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla and poppy seed and blend until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
This tastes just like the bread served at Market Fare restaurant in Lancaster.
A very good, easy recipe.

title: "instant" dessert(russian cream with raspberries)
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and set aside.
Heat cream and sugar until sugar dissolves completely.
Add gelatin to cream mixture and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Check by coating the back of a spoon and check for granules.
Do not allow to boil! Remove from heat; add sour cream and vanilla and mix very well until smooth.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm several hours.
Unmold and serve strewn with fresh raspberries and Raspberry Sauce.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add water and remaining vegetables.
Simmer until cooked. Add chicken and cook about 10 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon in hot mixture. Rinse frozen peas and add to mixture along with the soup. Cool before topping with uncooked pie crust.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes. Lower heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let sit to room temperature for awhile.
Mix all together. Make into 1-inch balls (approximately).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Put 1/2 carton of sour cream on top of broccoli.
Place bite-size chicken on top of sour cream.
Mix together whipping cream, other half of sour cream and soup mix.
Spread on top of chicken, then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 8.

title: chickaroni salad
directions: Blend soup, lemon juice and salt.
Combine with remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza(appetizer)
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet, sealing the seams with fingers.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley dressing together. Spread on cooled crust.
Chop vegetables fine and put on pizza crust.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Cut in squares.
Serve.

title: mushroom lasagne alfredo
directions: Prepare Alfredo sauce.
Triple recipe for lasagne.
Add sauteed mushrooms to sauce.

title: parsley chicken balls
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into balls. Roll in parsley and finely chopped nuts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; mix soup, butter, seasoning, peas, tuna and enough milk to cover bottom of casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Cover casserole and cook at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well and cook on medium heat until all is one ball.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: happiness cake
directions: Blend thoroughly the first 5 ingredients.
Fold together sacrificial giving and kindly service.
Gently mix altogether and season with tears of joy, sorrow and compassion.
Laughter will rise when mixture is correct.
Time redeemed wisely will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.
Omit all fault finding of self and others.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, flour, yolks, spices and vanilla.
Add boiling milk to this and beat with a beater until thoroughly mixed.
Add beaten egg whites and continue to beat until fluffy. Some may like a solid pie; this may just take a heated but not boiled milk and less beating.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in hot oven 15 minutes, then medium oven 45 minutes until done. Makes 3 pies.

title: corn flake kisses(1940)
directions: Fold ingredients together, except egg whites, then gradually add egg whites.
Drop on an oiled baking sheet with a teaspoon. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: wanda's hot chocolate
directions: Mix all together. Use 2 to 4 tablespoons per cup of boiling water. Yields approximately 100 cups.

title: ham chowder
directions: Saute onions, ham, celery and potatoes on low heat for 10 minutes (in melted margarine).
Stir in flour until blended.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly; bring to simmer or until chowder is thickened.
Do not boil.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Spread with butter, peanut butter and sliced banana.

title: patio chicken
directions: Put rice on bottom of buttered large 9 x 15-inch Pyrex dish. In saucepan, heat cream soup, water and onion soup mix.
Pour hot soup mixture over rice, being sure all rice is covered.
Lay chicken pieces on rice and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
(Can brush chicken with melted butter before last 20 minutes of baking.)

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and seasoning; drain. Add beans and soup; mix.
Put into large casserole.
Cook and mash potatoes or instant potatoes may be used.
Whip into mashed potatoes, milk and egg.
Spoon potatoes over casserole and top with grated cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Use the same water that you have soaked the beans in overnight.
Cover them and cook until tender.
Mix together melted butter, sour cream, molasses, dry mustard and the pinch of sugar. Pour this mixture over limas in a covered casserole dish and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple salad
directions: Cut apples into small chunks.
Mix apples, celery, raisins and cheese together.
In small bowl, mix salad dressing, peanut butter and brown sugar together.
Pour this mixture over apple mixture. Stir.

title: three step cheese cake
directions: Mix all until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and refrigerate several hours.
Add topping of your choice after it's cooled or leave plain.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together well, and form into small balls.
Roll in 12 ounces semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1/2 bar paraffin wax. Place on waxed paper until cool.
Do not pour remaining chocolate mixture down drain.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook milk, cocoa, salt, butter, sugar and vanilla to boiling. Boil 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop onto wax paper or buttered surface.
Wait until hardened.

title: butter crisps
directions: Cream butter, gradually add powdered sugar until fluffy.
Sift together the flour and salt.
Add 1 cup flour to creamed mixture. Add egg and vanilla, blend well.
Add remaining flour mixture.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix tomato juice and other ingredients.
Cook down to blend spices and to thicken a little.
Put into jars and process (hot water bath) for 10 minutes to seal jars.

title: low-fat cabbage and apple salad
directions: Combine cabbage, raisins, apple and yogurt in a medium bowl. Stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix in order: butter, brown sugar, eggs, raisins, flour, baking soda dissolved in water, nuts and spices.
On cookie sheet, drop by teaspoon, not too close together.
They spread as they bake.
Bake in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: In first bowl, break up cake to donut hole size pieces.
In second bowl, dissolve jello in water and add strawberries. Refrigerate until it shakes.
Whip cream and fold into jello.
Add jello mixture and cake pieces together.
Put in oiled tube pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together 1 cup brown sugar, butter, 3 teaspoons cinnamon and nuts and set aside.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread and cube.
Slice cheese into thin pieces.
Layer bread and cheese in buttered casserole dish.

title: zucchini pie(reduced fat)
directions: In a pie plate, beat eggs and add oil.
Stir together.
Add onions, grated cheese, Bisquick and mix.
Fold in zucchini, add parsley and stir full mixture.
Bake in same pie plate at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wonton soup
directions: Brown ground pork.
Combine with egg, onion, 2 teaspoons salt and 1 tablespoon
soy sauce.
Wrap small amount of meat mixture in wonton skin; fold in triangle and wet edge with water to stick together.
Combine chicken stock, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 2 teaspoons salt.
Add filled wontons and simmer until heated through.

title: waikiki chicken
directions: Coat chicken in flour, salt and pepper; brown in pan.
Drain off excess oil.
Combine pineapple, sauce, cornstarch and ginger; pour over chicken in skillet.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes on low heat.

title: quiche
directions: Put crumbled meat in crust, add grated cheese over meat. Sprinkle onion over meat and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and spices. Whip until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Remove skin from chicken in ungreased baking pan.
Spread 1 teaspoon butter on each piece.
Sprinkle with onion, garlic salt and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add the chicken pieces.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: sugartown's blueberry pie
directions: Wash and drain berries. Mix all ingredients together and pour into 1 crust. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes (keep heat low).
Cool.
Fold in berries.
Put mixture into baked, cooled pie shell.

title: potato soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Store in airtight container (2 1/2 cups).
To 1/4 cup, mix and add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Let soup set 1 to 2 minutes to thicken slightly.

title: barbecued pork loin roast
directions: Have backbone removed from loin.
Place fat side up in an open roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer so bulb reaches thickest part, being sure it does not rest in fat or on bone.
Do not add water.
Do not cover.
Roast in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Mix together sauce ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Continue roasting about 1 hour or until roast thermometer registers 185°, basting with sauce every 20 minutes.
(Sauce is excellent; we usually make a double recipe.)

title: mandarin orange truffle
directions: In a food blender, chop oranges very fine.
In a saucepan, combine oranges, chocolate chips, milk and oleo.
Heat until chips melt; cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in crushed vanilla wafers, sugar, almonds and liqueur.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Mixture will be firm.
Shape into balls; roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Put in fridge in a covered container.

title: southwest taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°. Partially bake pie crust for 10 minutes; cool. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain fat. Stir in taco seasoning mix.

title: cream cheese chip dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Chill before serving. Works best with deli-dippers (tortilla chips).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute bell pepper, onions and celery in cooking oil.
Add chili powder, salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 30 minutes; add shrimp and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: angel fruit delight(low-fat)
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Arrange half the cake in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with half of the undrained pineapple and cherries.
Spread half of the Cool Whip over it and top with half the coconut.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip and coconut.
Cover and chill overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: braised beef
directions: Cut meat into one inch cubes. Brown with onions in hot fat in Dutch oven or other heavy skillet. Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water and add with remaining ingredients. Cover and cook over slow heat until meat is tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours; or use a covered casserole dish in a 300° oven. Add more water as needed. Thicken liquid, if desired, with a paste made of flour and water. Makes 4 servings. A 4 ounce can of sliced or button mushrooms may be added, if desired.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix and lemon pudding, then add eggs, lemon extract, lemon juice and oil.
Beat with mixer well.
Cook on 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
While cake is cooking make the glaze.

title: grammy finocchiaro's french crepes
directions: Beat with electric mixer or whisk; batter is thin.
Fry in pan greased lightly.
Spread with jam or our favorite, fresh sliced strawberries and a little Cool Whip.
Roll up and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
(Frozen strawberries are yummy, too.)

title: the recipe
directions: Mix water and sugar in pan.
Bring to a boil and add tea bags. Let cool. Add orange juice and lemonade.
Stir in bourbon. Put in ice cream pail or plastic container and put in deep freeze.

title: microwaved baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a microwave-safe dish with a lid.
Cover and heat on Medium-high for about 7 minutes. Leave cover on until ready to serve.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Roll into balls and stick toothpicks into them.
Place on cookie sheets.
Freeze for 1 to 2 hours.

title: great punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: susan's quiche recipe
directions: In 8-inch greased pan, place croutons in bottom of pan. Add cheese
on	top
of
croutons.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, mustard and
onion	powder	and blend.
Pour on top of cheese. Top with crumbled
bacon.
Bake,
uncovered,
at
325° for 60 minutes.

title: frankfurter bake
directions: Saute onions in a little butter until golden.
Set aside. Drain sauerkraut and place on bottom of baking pan.
Spread mashed potatoes over sauerkraut.
Arrange frankfurters on potatoes. Arrange sauteed onions over frankfurters.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: In small bowl, combine tomato soup, sugar, vinegar and oil. Cut up all the vegetables and place in large bowl.
Mix in ingredients from small bowl, mix thoroughly.
Cover with Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 loaves.
Grease two 8 x 4-inch of 9 x 5-inch pans with Pam.
Bake for 60 minutes.
When bread is finished, remove from pans immediately and cool on cookie racks.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add nuts.
Melt shortening, mix in brown sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture. Spread in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake at 350° 20-25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Let cool before cutting. Store in airtight container to maintain freshness.

title: beet luncheon salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 pint hot water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened, then fold in beets, cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Turn into molds.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: pasta fagiole
directions: Saute garlic and chopped romaine in small amount of oil.
Add sauce and beans.
Add pasta along with 2 cups of salted cooking water.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix margarine, oil and spices.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Combine dry ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Pour margarine over dry ingredients slowly, while stirring.
Bake for 2 hours at 200°, stirring often.
Store in airtight containers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries through food grinder and pour sugar over and let stand while preparing other ingredients or about an hour.
Add marshmallows, grapes and pecans and fold in whipping cream at last.
This can be frozen, keeps well.

title: brown paper bag pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except apples, pie shell and lemon juice) to coat apples.
Put apples into pie shell and drizzle lemon juice over them.
Sprinkle topping over apples, then slice into a heavy brown paper shopping bag (bag must not touch the top of the pie).
Double fold the end of the bag and fasten with paper clips. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Split bag open immediately.
Cool.
This is a great way to save your oven from pie spills.
The pie always turns out perfect.

title: no fat potato salad for two
directions: Cool potato and dice for potato salad.	Add celery, pepper, onion and pickle.
In a small bowl or cup combine the pickle juice, mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour over potato and mix well.

title: garlic lover's pasta of the angels
directions: Start cooking pasta.
At the same time, pour olive oil into 12-inch skillet and add garlic.
Cook garlic slowly until tender. Add tomatoes with liquid, basil and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring 5 minutes.
Add pasta to the sauce a little at a time and mix thoroughly.
Reheat.
Top with Parmesan cheese and serve with salad and crusty bread.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: christmas candy
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and sugar with hands.
Make balls 1-inch in diameter.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brush chicken with melted butter and lemon juice.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Bake, skin side up, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Cook sausage with onion until onion is tender.
Add corn and rice.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon sausage/corn/rice mixture around chicken. Bake 30 minutes more.

title: fruit punch
directions: Empty frozen juices, pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water into large container.
Thaw and stir well.
Pour mixture into punch bowl; add ice cubes.
Just before serving, gently pour in ginger ale and soda water.
Top with fruit ice ring or other fruit garnishes.
Makes 30 servings.

title: creamy chicken or turkey
directions: Cook contents or rice and seasoning packets according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, pimento, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, onion and garlic salt in a bowl; spread over pizza tin for "crust."

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Mix together pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar for crust. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Combine melted butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add chocolate bits. Pour butterscotch bits. Pour Eagle Brand milk over top; add chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape mixture into patties.
Fry in hot oil in skillet over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip well with mixer.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with crushed peanuts. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Freeze.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients.
Put in greased casserole. Top with cornflake crumbs, dot with oleo and sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and squeezed lemon juice together.
Add boiling water to lemon jello and cool.
Mix with cream cheese mixture.
Whip the milk and add to the mixture.

title: grits and cheese
directions: Cook grits in boiling water for 6 minutes; add butter and beaten eggs.
Add all seasonings and grated cheese, mixing well. Pour into greased baking dish and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, until top is golden.
(This may be frozen before baking.)
Serves 10.

title: shrimp and crab delight
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery in butter until celery is tender.
Add Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In a large bowl thoroughly mix shrimp, stuffing mix, mayonnaise and crab meat.
Mix in hot sauce, eggs and garlic powder.
Add other ingredients, mix and pour into 9 x 13 x 2 inch buttered pan. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zesty horseradish corn-on-the-cob
directions: Prepare grill or heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, stir together all ingredients except corn.
Spread about 1 tablespoon butter mixture evenly over each ear of corn.
Wrap tightly in heavy-duty double thickness aluminum foil, sealing well.
Place on grill rack directly over coals or low flame, turning every 5 minutes for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
If baking, place foil-wrapped corn on jelly roll pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: *impossible quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble it.
Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over the bottom of the pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in the center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftover quiche.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ground chuck casserole
directions: Saute chuck, onion and pepper together.
Drain off excess fat. Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Place half of noodles in large casserole dish.
Layer meat, corn, soup, cheese and olives, stacking like pudding.
Repeat layers and add 2/3 cup of water to dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.

title: cauliflower-grape salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients together; pour over cauliflower, grapes and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: ham sandwich delights
directions: Blend together butter, onion, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire.
Cut off top 1/3 of rolls.
Spread both sides with butter mixture.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom of rolls.
Put tops back on and freeze well.
(Wrap in aluminum foil.)
Cut into individual sandwiches and arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with a vegetable peeler or knife, if desired.
Cook asparagus, covered, in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain and place in a shallow dish. Combine vinegar and next 6 ingredients; pour over asparagus. Cover and chill 8 hours.
Remove from marinade and, if desired, serve in "bundles" in lemon rind rings.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put raw hamburger in 9 x 13 pan until covers bottom of pan. Sprinkle onion over meat. Combine the soups in bowl along with green beans and some liquid. Stir and pour over onions. Place cheese slices on top of soup (optional). Cover with Tater Tots in rows as close together as possible so entire casserole is covered. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Do not add salt to this recipe.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag or a bowl.
Cut up meat into strips.
Shake or roll meat strips in flour mix.
Heat canola oil in frypan or Dutch oven.
Fry steak strips until nice and brown.
Add onion.
Cook until golden color.
Stir in flour remaining from flouring meat.
Add consomme, water and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream and chives. Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Serve over cooked wide noodles or rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water and add bay leaf, onion, garlic, salt and pepper and bouillon.
Cook until chicken falls off bone. Remove chicken from broth.
Remove chicken from bone.
Bring broth back to boil and then add dumplings.
Cut the shortening into dry ingredients.
Add enough hot broth to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough out on well floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 1-inch strips and cut into 4-inch pieces.
Drop one at a time into hot broth.
Cook until tender, 15 minutes.
Add boned chicken to dumplings.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball or roll. Chill before serving. Serve on crackers.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in buttered casserole.
Mix topping and spread over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: santa fe pita pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly brush bread with oil.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour and baking powder.
Beat 1 egg.
Add 1/2 cup water and 2 teaspoons lemon juice; add to flour/lard mixture. This will keep in icebox for several weeks.
Makes 3 double crust pies.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pie filling in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Bake 30 minutes.
May be served warm or cool.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix in blender, then cook down to a thick sauce.

title: chicken caruso and rice
directions: Season chicken with garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute in butter 2 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and Italian seasoning.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery.
Continue cooking until celery is tender.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: In a gallon container, mix Kool-Aid, juice and sugar. Add water, leaving enough space at top for shaking room. Freeze for a while, then go back and shake. Set out several hours before serving.

title: yogurt muffins
directions: Stir with fork until mixes well.
Add 1/2 cube melted margarine.
Stir until just moistened with fruit yogurt.
Use cupcake papers in muffin pan.
Fill 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients but nuts with an electric mixer.
Shape into a ball.
This is a very soft mixture.
Roll in crushed nuts that have been put on waxed paper.
Shape into a ball using the waxed paper.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Flavor improves with age.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the water and put in the pudding.
Mix in the Cool Whip.
Add the pineapple.
Put between the layers of the cake and on top.
Top with the nuts and cherries.

title: turkey dip
directions: Rub container with garlic and layer in order.

title: icebox tea cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla, nutmeg, salt and vinegar.
Mix until well blended.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder; add to mixture.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into silver dollar size rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until ready to bake.
Slice thin.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, 8 to 10 minutes (350°) or until light brown.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans. Pour vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and oil over beans.
Mix well; let stand overnight.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter or margarine, oil, granulated sugar and powdered sugar. Add the vanilla and eggs. Blend in the baking soda, flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Chill.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until brown on bottom.

title: microwave golden chicken
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up in 2-quart glass baking dish. Sprinkle with celery and salt.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: eggless applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Sift the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cocoa.
Mix in the applesauce.
(Raisins may be added.)
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch on low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add Jell-O; cook until clear.
Arrange strawberries in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries.
Cool completely; top with Cool Whip.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add 3/4 cup cold water and mix well.
Chill to egg white consistency.	Stir in 3 cups peaches, 1 tablespoon sugar, sliced banana and chopped pecans. Pour into 8-cup mold and
chill
until set.
Soften Knox gelatine in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Scald the half and half and stir into gelatine.
Beat
remaining
ingredients together and join with
half	and
half
mixture.
Pour
the	well-blended mixture over the jello and chill at least 8 hours.

title: quick cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients into a ball.
Roll into crushed nuts.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sticky barbecue chicken
directions: Prepare chicken to fry.
In a large skillet, fry chicken until done.
Drain all oil from skillet.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onions, salt and egg and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Blend in remaining soup, water and 2 to 3 tablespoons drippings.
Heat; stir often. Serve with meat loaf.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Recipe makes enough batter for 6 pieces boned chicken or 8 chicken cutlets (cutlets preferred).

title: cranberry punch
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Store in refrigerator and heat as needed.

title: turkey-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute the celery and onions; combine all ingredients and spread bread crumbs and margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles and is fully warmed, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bryant's "secret" cookie recipe
directions: Add a few drops of hot water for mixing ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until very light brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in a crock and cover them with one handful of	salt.
Let
stand
overnight.
Drain
and
add sugar, white mustard
seed and cloves.
Cover with vinegar and cook 10 or 15	minutes.
Don't let pickles cook fast, just let them heat through real
good.
Pack
in
quart
jars and seal. This is an old-time recipe my grandma used.

title: red hot tomato soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil and butter in large saucepan or kettle.
Cook until translucent.
Add salt, peppers, honey and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 1 hour on low heat.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add celery, onions, and green pepper. Add soups and liquids. Mix well and add rice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered. Then another hour uncovered.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter, add chocolate.
Stir over low heat until melted. Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and corn syrup, stirring until dissolved.
Cook 5 minutes and add vanilla and salt.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican bean spread
directions: Blend in a food processor, adding more catsup if needed for desired consistency. Makes about 1 1/4 cups (serving size is 2 ounces or 1/2 cup). Contains 90 calories per serving.

title: cherry cream
directions: In a 3-cup glass mixing bowl, combine the gelatin and water. Heat mixture in the microwave oven until the water is hot enough to dissolve the gelatin, 3 or 4 minutes.
(If you prefer, boil the water on top of the stove.)
Add 5 or 6 ice cubes and stir the mixture with a wire whip until the ice is melted and the mixture is cooled.
Add the yogurt and continue stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add water or cherries to fill the bowl.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve with more cherries, if desired.

title: bill bailey corn bread
directions: Mix together and pour into greased pan.
Good baked in iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix and heat soups, Ro-Tel and shrimp until shrimp are thoroughly heated. Put cooked rice into large casserole dish and pour shrimp mixture over it.
Serve hot with salad and hot rolls.

title: zesty grilled pork chops
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Place chops in a glass baking dish and pour marinade over them.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 12 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, cheese and Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Mix together pudding mixture and cream cheese mixture.
Smash a 1 pound package of Oreo cookies.
Put half in bottom of pan.
Pour in filling. Use rest of crumbs on top.
(Can use any cream filled cookies.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease pie plate with margarine.
Peel and slice apples. Combine rest of ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black bottom pies
directions: Sift together flour, 2 cups sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add water, cooking oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful of this mixture onto cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and let stand while you make a double crust. Before putting on top crust, cover filling with miniature marshmallows.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange the sweet potatoes in a shallow baking dish. Combine margarine and cinnamon and pour over potatoes. Arrange the apricot halves on top. Cover and bake in a 425 degree oven for about 15 minutes. Add the orange slices and serve.

title: cranberry apple punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Prepare tea.
Refrigerate all.
Mix just before serving.
Garnish with ice ring (6 to 6 1/2-inch), citrus slices and cherries or strawberries.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients. Pour into ungreased loaf pan. Top with ketchup if desired. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients to gather and store in the refrigerator, to set.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
Lay lasagna out flat.
Cook spinach as directed on box; drain well.
Mix spinach with Ricotta.
Spoon on strips of lasagna.
Roll like strudel.
Stand upright in casserole dish so you can see curls and filling.
Repeat until dish is filled.
Cover with tomato sauce and chopped onion.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ooee gooee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix will be crumbly.

title: beef nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in refried beans, salt, pepper, tomato sauce and jalapeno peppers.
Heat through. Arrange chips on a plate.
Spoon beef/bean mixture on chips; sprinkle tomatoes, olives and cheese on top.

title: my old lemon pie(fifty-five years old)
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Then add cornstarch moistened with water, stirring as you add starch.
Return and cook 3 minutes.
Add egg yolks, salt, lemon juice and rind, stirring at all times.
Cool slightly.
Pour into shell.
Cover with well-beaten meringue and lightly brown in oven.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook sugar, water and butter until it spins a thread in cold water.
Drop by spoonfuls on wet board or cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon in bowl, stir in one egg and approximately one tablespoon of either self-rising flour or cornmeal.
An optional addition is one small diced onion.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot oil until brown on one side, then turn and brown on the other side.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In large Dutch oven combine beans with 6 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Add 8 cups water, hocks, spices and onion.
Bring to boil (covered).
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Bone hocks; return to beans with vegetables and potato flakes. Stir to blend.
Simmer several hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf.

title: almond butter balls
directions: Mix well.
Form small balls by rolling in hand.
Dip in xxxx sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: In dutch oven or crock pot mix all ingredients except beets, bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes uncovered.
Add beets to hot liquid.
Cover and let cool.
Refrigerate stirring once a day for 4-5 days.
Serve cold, store in refrigerator.
Be careful-this mixture will stain.

title: cheese dip for vegetables
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients, using an electric mixer.
Mix well.
Blend in cream cheese.
Serve, chilled, as a dip with vegetables.
(I've become famous for this one!)

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown onion, meat and salt; pour in casserole.
Place celery and peas over meat.
Mix mushroom soup with small amount of milk; add soy sauce.
Pour over mixture and cover with Chinese noodles. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add broccoli; pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until set or about 30 minutes.
Cover with chips or onion rings and bake until light brown (about 5 minutes).

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar,
coconut and chopped nuts. Chill for a while in bowl.
Form	into
small
balls and chill again on greased cookie sheet.
Melt
chocolate
chips and wax together and dip.
Place on cookie sheet to set.

title: hamburger and cabbage
directions: Brown hamburger and add seasonings.
Drain.
Cut cabbage in chunks; lay in pan.
Place hamburger over the top.
Cover with soup and juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or in slow cooker on low until cabbage is tender.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: cheese cake cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
In small bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in melted butter until well combined.
Reserve 1/3 cup.
Put remaining mixture evenly into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak #2
directions: Brown
steaks
in
14-inch Dutch oven in the margarine. Add chopped
onions
and
celery.
Stir
in
the
rest	of the ingredients and cook for one hour with 12 coals on the top and 14 coals on the bottom.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let stand 1 hour.
Boil together sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, water and vinegar for 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage and mix.
Cool and freeze.

title: green pepper boats
directions: Cut a thin slice from the top of each green pepper.
Cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
In a saucepan, cook pepper halves in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Invert and drain peppers on paper towels.

title: cherry delights
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar until light and fluffy; add syrup, egg
yolks
and flour.
Stir until blended well;
chill. Roll into
inch balls.
Coat each with egg white and roll in pecans.
Place
on
a
greased baking sheet.
Press cherry half into center of each ball.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix well the first seven ingredients and divide into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Bake in ungreased Pyrex dish for 30 minutes at 350°. Drain well.
In separate bowl, mix grape jelly and shrimp cocktail sauce. Pour over meat balls and put back in oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Set aside to cool.
Add olives, onions, pineapple and bell peppers and reheat until peppers are done.

title: red beans and rice party dip
directions: Prepare beans and rice according to package directions. Add salsa and peppers. Stir. Place mixture in blender. Grind until texture is smooth.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine sugar and 1 cup water in saucepan.
Cook, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining water, lime juice and lime rind; chill.
Spoon sherbet into punch.
Add lemon-lime beverage. Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: the best scones
directions: Remove butter from refrigerator 25 minutes before preparing scones to soften.
Preheat oven to 425°.

Place flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and sugar in a large bowl and stir to blend. Using a pastry blender, cut butter into flour mixture, lifting the flour to aerate as you work. Use a light touch for light scones.

title: nutty noodly - chocolate clusters
directions: Melt and stir chips over low heat until completely dissolved. Remove from heat and add nuts and noodles, so they are evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper and put in refrigerator until hard.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Boil, cool, skin and debone chickens.
Mix soups, chickens, garlic, chilies and sour cream.
Line 11 x 14-inch baking dish with tortillas; spread 1/3 of chicken mixture.
Make another layer of tortillas; spread with more of chicken mixture.
Top the last layer of tortillas with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel nut pie
directions: Crack and separate eggs while they are cold.
Then let stand until room temperature.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and baking powder.
Continue beating until all sugar is added and egg whites form peaks.
By hand, add crushed crackers and pecans and fold into egg white mixture.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled, use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Mix milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut; simmer 1 minute.
Punch holes in cake and pour hot mixture over cake.
Mix 1/2 c. coconut with Cool Whip and ice cake with this mixture.
Keep refrigerated. Keeps for several days.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute garlic, onion, carrot, celery and potatoes in oil.
Add the remaining ingredients together in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan, cooking until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts, cooking until mixture reaches hard crack stage.
Stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour into well-greased bendable cookie sheet or aluminum pie plates.
Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: barbecued deer
directions: Boil roast with celery and onion.
Cut across the grain in small pieces.
Place in baking dish.
Add chopped onions and barbecue sauce.
If meat looks dry, add cooking oil.
Bake until barbecue sauce is absorbed.

title: pretzel pie
directions: Melt enough oleo to mix.
Place in bottom of pan.
Add Dream Whip as to directions on box.
Next layer cream cheese to which 1/2 cup sugar is added.
Mix all and place on top of crust.
For topping, use either pineapple or strawberry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and margarine (melted). Add sugar and flavoring.
Add nuts and mix well, then pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 or 50 minutes.
Makes a large pie.

title: sweet potato boats
directions: Let potatoes cool after baking; cut in half (lengthwise). Scoop out inside, saving the peelings.
Mash potato, brown sugar and peanut butter together.
Put back into peelings.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Put into oven at 450° and brown slightly.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Melt sugar in large pot, adding 1/2 cup canned milk or just enough to melt sugar, then add vanilla.
Let come to boil.
Add peanut butter, beating until creamy and smooth.
Spread over layers.

title: perfectly parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In saucepan, heat half and half, butter and salt.
Spread potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour heated mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 60 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add granulated sugar, brown sugar, butter, water, vanilla and beaten egg.
Beat the mixture until it looks smooth.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed camels
directions: Skin, trim and clean camel (once you get over the hump), lamb and chickens.
Boil until tender.
Cook rice until fluffy.
Fry nuts until brown and mix with rice.
Hard-boil eggs and peel. Stuff cooked chickens with hard-boiled eggs and rice; stuff the cooked lamb with stuffed chickens.
Add more rice; stuff the camel with the stuffed lamb and add the rest of the rice.
Broil over large charcoal pit until brown.
Spread any remaining rice on large tray and place camel on top of rice.
Decorate with boiled eggs and nuts.
Serves a friendly crowd of 80 to 100.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop
by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and press down with fork.	Bake at 325° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: marble cake
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Save out 1/3 of batter.
Pour other into tube pan.
Mix with saved batter 1/4 cup chocolate syrup.
Spoon this on top of cake and zigzag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched. Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats.
Add oleo and cover with towel.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir all together and bake in 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions. Drain. To keep cooked shells from sticking together, place them on waxed paper in a single layer. In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except sauce. Mix well. Fill pasta shells with cheese mixture, using a 1 1/2 Tbsp. for each shell. Spread 1/2 cup of sauce on the bottom of a 6x10 inch baking dish. Place shells in pan, cheese side up. Spoon remaining sauce evenly over shells. Cover tightly and bake 35 minutes in a 350 degrees oven. Yields 6 servings.

title: flounder ala maison(penrose diner)
directions: Beat eggs in a small bowl; set aside.
Dip flounder in flour and then dip in eggs.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add flounder and saute until golden brown on both sides. Add broccoli, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Continue to saute until vegetables are tender, approximately 8 minutes.
When this is completed, add the cup of cream and wine.
Cook approximately 3 more minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2 people.

title: crabmeat mornay
directions: Melt oleo in heavy pot and saute onions, bell pepper, celery and parsley.
I often substitute 1/2 carrot, finely chopped and sauteed for pimento.
Blend in flour, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Add evaporated milk or cream and simmer for 2 minutes.
Gently fold in crabmeat, picked over.
Add sherry just before serving. Yields 5 1/2 cups, 75 pattie shells or 1 1/2 to 2 boxes Melba rounds.

title: baked pumpkin seeds
directions: Soak seeds for 15 to 30 minutes in just enough water to cover. Use 1 teaspoon salt to each cup seeds.
Drain, spread on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt and bake for about 1 hour at 250° or until toasted.

title: cornwallville pickles
directions: You will need a 1 gallon glass jar.

title: baked beans
directions: Open can of beans; place in a casserole dish.
Add sugar, catsup and bacon on top.
Bake at 350°
for about 45 minutes and serve.

title: winter squash casserole
directions: Grease or spray a small casserole dish.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble into squash.
Fry onion in 1 tablespoon of drippings until transparent.
Add to the squash.
Add grated cheese, salt and Tabasco or pepper.
Mix well.
Transfer to prepared baking dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 325° or 350° oven, until heated through and crumbs begin to brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a deep 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan or two 9-inch round cake pans; melt butter.
Add brown sugar and stir over low heat, until dissolved.
Arrange pineapples and cherries into bottom of pans.
Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Fill prepared pan 3/4 full and bake 30 to 40 minutes. Any remaining cake mix can be used for cup cakes.
When cake is done and still hot, run a knife around cake edge and invert on a serving plate.

title: pork patties
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Soak bread or cracker crumbs in milk and egg.
Add meat, onion and seasonings.
Shape into patties and fry.

title: mom's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix last.

title: freezer lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion in olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients through bay leaf.
Simmer at least 1 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat margarine and soup, then mix in sour cream. Season with cheese on top. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan until bubbles on top. Or top with chips, broccoli, cooked chicken burger.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle with chopped onions.
If you like black olives you can add a layer sliced on top of sour cream along with chopped green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over this and pour remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine first five ingredients with half of the juice.
Mix lightly and make 1 1/2 inch (about 18) balls.
Place balls in skillet.
Combine remaining juice and sugar; pour over balls. Bring all to boil, reduce and simmer, covered, 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Put 1/2 apple into each piece of crust.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar, pat of butter and sprinkle of cinnamon to each.
Wrap apple in crust.
Turn upside down in buttered dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and cook until a soft ball. Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and a small amount of red food coloring if you want to.
Pour on buttered wax paper and cool.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together for 24 hours.

title: christmas applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift 1 3/4 cups flour with spices, soda and baking powder.
Add applesauce alternately with flour mixture.
Beat well.
Mix remaining flour with raisins and walnuts.
Fold raisins, nuts and vanilla into batter last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Pour
ingredients
into a casserole and mix thoroughly. Layer pieces
of	chicken over top and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Wash potatoes carefully; cook in a covered saucepan until soft.
Peel and mash in a medium sized bowl.
(You should get about 1/2 cup of mashed potatoes.)
Add other ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 150° until lightly browned.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with crushed corn flakes and butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: city chicken "legs"
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 inch squares. Thread meat on 12 small skewers to form "legs". Roll in flour and in eggs beaten with water; roll in bread crumbs. Melt shortening in frying pan and brown meat.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add cornflakes, oatmeal, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When cake is done, pierce with 2-prong fork.

title: accordion potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Peel potatoes and drop into cold water. Cut potatoes into thin slices, but do not cut all the way through. Place a wooden spoon in front of the potato and cut only until the knife connects with the spoon handle.
Drop potatoes back into the cold water until all are sliced.
Drain and pat them dry. Generously oil 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange potatoes, sliced side up, in a single layer.
Brush with half the butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Add remaining butter to baking dish and baste potatoes occasionally.
Dust with Parmesan and paprika and roast another 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Potatoes should have opened like a fan.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Using mallet, lightly
beat
chicken slices to flatten. Cut each slice of cheese
into	four pieces (about the size of the chicken strips).
Cut
the	ham
the
same way.
Layer the chicken, ham and cheese, and
roll up.
Secure the roll with a toothpick.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Mash banana or beat until creamy. Beat in sugar and part of milk until mixture is smooth. Add rest of milk and vanilla. Chill.

title: cracker jacks
directions: In large pan, mix together popcorn and peanuts.
In a saucepan, mix together butter, brown sugar, Karo syrup and molasses.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Mix well.
Add to popcorn and peanuts.
Mix well until coated.
Put into two 12 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread refried beans over bottom.
Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Add taco seasoning and water; simmer according to directions on package. Mix together egg, sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Drop on top of meat mixture and spread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until edges brown.
Serve with chopped lettuce, onions, tomatoes and salsa.

title: tasty corn salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine sugar, vinegar and garlic powder; stir until sugar dissolves. Pour over vegetables, tossing gently.
Cover tightly and chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse kraut and drain.
Chop vegetables and mix with kraut. Mix vinegar, oil, water and sugar.
Pour over kraut and blend well.
Chill at least overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: fried fruit salad
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Cook apples for 3 minutes.
Add pineapple.
Cook an additional 3 minutes.
Add bananas and cook just until warmed through.
Remove from heat and toss with remaining ingredients and serve.

title: rum glaze
directions: In a small bowl combine powdered sugar, butter and rum (or milk).
Stir in whipping cream or milk.
If necessary, add cream or milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, until it reaches drizzle consistency.

title: spicy barbecue spareribs
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a large shallow dish.
Add ribs; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, turning ribs occasionally.
Drain ribs and reserve marinade.
Place ribs, bone side down, on grill over slow coals.
Grill 30 minutes, turning ribs frequently.
Brush with sauce.
Cook additional 30 minutes, basting and turning frequently.

title: cream of wheat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well (best mixed with your hands).
Form for your choice of baking pan.
Bake uncovered on 400° for approximately 45 min.
