Drain excess grease.
Top with ketchup and bake 5 more min.

title: holiday cookie pizza
directions: Mix ingredients.
Knead until soft dough.
Press into bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of greased 12-inch round pan.

title: vanilla pudding grahamwiches(makes 22 sandwiches)
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: creamy slaw
directions: Shred cabbage very fine.
Slice onion very fine or thin and then separate the rings. Toss these two together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegetable medley quiche
directions: In medium skillet, over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add zucchini and peppers.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp.
Spoon mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Mix Egg Beaters, skim milk and seasonings.
Pour over filling in crust. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted into middle of filling.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onions in oil until done.
Cook ground beef and add to it.
Stir in taco seasoning, tomatoes, olives and chilies.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread 1 cup nacho chips on bottom of dish.
Spoon meat mix, sprinkle cheese over, spread sour cream over and sprinkle remaining chips. Bake 25 minutes. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese atop. Bake 5 minutes more. Take it out of the oven and pig out.

title: easy cocoa mix
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl.
Store in covered container.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage in large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat. Add onion; cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour; cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings; cook and stir until thickened.
Great served over biscuits and scrambled eggs.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Place in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet on medium-high.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add remaining Scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettuccini; toss and heat through.

title: shrimp creole(serves 4)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan and save.
Add onion and peppers to bacon fat and simmer until tender; add tomatoes, crushed, and seasonings.
Chop bacon real fine; add to mixture and let simmer over a low heat about 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 15 minutes longer; serve over rice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini in thin round slices.

Fry ground beef with onion. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking oil. Layer zucchini, beef, noodles and cheese until you end up with zucchini on top with remaining cheese on top of the zucchini. Pour tomato soup on top and the 1 1/2 cans of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil. Dissolve Jell-O in this. Remove from heat. Add cherries, juice and Coca-Cola. Congeal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle more Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a medium sized skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium high heat and saute the garlic, onion, celery and carrots.
Add the flour, sugar, salt, 1 teaspoon dried basil, pepper and broth and bring to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Reduce heat.
Add the peas and simmer for 5 minutes, still stirring.
Stir in the chicken, mix all together and pour the mixture into a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.

title: campbell's 1-dish chicken and rice bake
directions: Mix soup, water, rice, paprika and pepper in 2-quart shallow baking dish. Top with chicken. Season with additional paprika and pepper. Cover. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix until light first 3 ingredients.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a baked Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust and chill.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Shape into balls and place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole pan.
Mix 1 cup ketchup and 1 cup water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and blend thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts; makes a stiff dough.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and open the door and let cake stay in oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: country apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla until well blended.
Beat in flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt. When completely mixed, batter will be very thick.
Stir in nuts and apples.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll by spoonful into balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Break strawberries into halves and add to water.
Spread half of this mix into a 9 x 9-inch dish. Slice banana and arrange slices on top of mixture.
Press the banana in slightly.
Cover banana with sour cream.
Add rest of Jell-O mixture to form top layer.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix with remaining ingredients, but add apples last.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.

title: walnut pudding
directions: Combine brown sugar, water and oleo.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour on top of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: bernadine's okra dressing
directions: Cook okra in oil until slime is out.
Saute onion, bell pepper and tomato.
Cut sausage, bacon and ham into small pieces and cook partially.
Drain on paper toweling to remove excess fat.
Cook ground pork or beef until pink color is removed.
Add all ingredients together and cook additional 45 minutes on medium to low heat. Add rice to desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican egg pockets
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk, chives and salt.
In a 7 to 8-inch omelet pan or skillet over medium heat, heat butter until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Pour in egg mixture. As mixture begins to set, gently draw an inverted pancake turner completely across bottom and sides of pan, forming large, soft curds.
Continue until eggs are thickened, but still moist.
Do not stir constantly.
Place pita bread halves upright in loaf pan. Fill each half with 1/4 of the cooked eggs, tomatoes, pepper and onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven just until cheese is melted, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Top each pita half with 1 teaspoon taco sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato paste; put into loaf pan.
Spread tomato paste evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let set 20 minutes while you mix next ingredients.
Cream butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal if 20 minutes is up.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Pour all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into ungreased pan and sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: curried vegetable salad
directions: In covered saucepan cook turnips, carrots, cauliflowerets and green pepper.
Cook in a small amount of boiling, salted water about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp or tender.
Drain and cool.
Pour curry dressing over vegetables.
Toss to coat vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: country brown beans
directions: Soak beans 3 hours before preparation.
Brown chuck before adding to mixture.
Saute onions and peppers before starting.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients, except raisins. Stir in raisins. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate or maple fudge
directions: Note:
Maple fudge same as chocolate, only omit cocoa.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a large kettle.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and tomato soup.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: la groceria's chicken verdicchio
directions: Heat the vegetable oil in a 12-inch saute pan on medium heat. Lightly flour the chicken.
Add the chicken to the pan and brown on both sides.
Discard the oil.
Add the butter, mushrooms and artichokes, cooking for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the white wine (if cooking over a
flame, remove the pan from the flame before adding the wine.
Cover and cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add the lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste and about 1 teaspoon of flour to thicken the sauce).
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes while stirring.
Add the roasted peppers and parsley and serve.
Serves approximately 3.

title: my grandmother's gingerbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening.
Add egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with water; beat well.
Bake at 350°.
Will be thin, but is very good.
I double recipe for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve
first
3 ingredients in 2 cups boiling water. Leave on simmer a few minutes to melt cream cheese and marshmallows. Then
beat	with
electric	mixer a few minutes. Add pineapple, juice
and	all.
Add
cup cold water and 1 cup (pecans)
nuts, chopped.
Mix
again.
Put
in
refrigerator. Keep stirring
once in
a
while.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan to set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix onion soup, French dressing and cranberry sauce together. Place raw chicken in casserole.
Pour mixture over chicken. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and continue to bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple streusel squares
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture. Add apples, hot water and nuts.
Put in greased 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown meat. Sprinkle soup mix over meat; stir in water. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Combine lettuce, tomato, onion, green pepper, olives and cheese; toss well. Place lettuce mixture on individual salad plates. Spoon on meat. Top with corn chips.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets and retain 1/2 cup beet juice.
Add beet juice, vinegar, sugar and cloves to beets and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Good served either hot or cold.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Cool and combine all ingredients.
Marinate 12 hours.
These keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Place a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer uncooked lasagna noodles.
Add layers of cheeses (Mozzarella, Parmesan and Ricotta).
Repeat all layers.
Do not let noodles touch sides of the dish.
Top layer should be Mozzarella cheese.

title: smush cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Pat in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cut small pieces; it's very rich.

title: little round meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, using just enough milk to moisten.
Keep for 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls; wrap in foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve sliced on Ritz crackers.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.

title: lamb patty stew
directions: Combine lamb, egg, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion and bread crumbs.
Make into patties, smaller than hamburger patties, about 1/2-inch thick.
Roll in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Slowly fry in ungreased frypan until brown on both sides. Put in bottom of casserole with tight cover.
Put in vegetables on top.
Pour catsup over all and let simmer a couple of hours. Casserole can be put in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Also I have used a bag of frozen (mixed) peas, carrots and lima beans instead of fresh vegetables.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and then flour slowly.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
If you don't have cake flour, use regular flour, but take out 2 tablespoons of flour per cup and add 2 tablespoons cornstarch per cup.

title: linda's green beans
directions: Prepare beans according to instructions and drain.
Be sure to use frozen beans as canned beans will not work.
In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat and saute onion, 2 to 3 minutes. Add cubed bread and saute until the bread is slightly brown and margarine is absorbed.
You may need to add more margarine as you should not leave any dry cubes.
Gently stir beans into the bread cubes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly, approximately 25 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, using two (8-inch) pans.
Cool and split each layer. Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Add chopped peaches and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Cool completely.

title: aunt sharon's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Marinate mushrooms in salad dressing for at least 1 hour, but no more than 1 1/2 hours; drain.
Remove stems.
Chop (fine) a few of the stems and mix the rest of the ingredients.
Stuff the caps. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jackie's cake
directions: Bake at 350° until brown in 3 pans, greased and floured.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk and eggs until creamy.
Stir in pineapple with liquid.
Pinch off bread and stir into mixture, 2 slices at a time.
Put into greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Boil beef stew chunks until tender.
Cook peeled potatoes until done.
Combine beef chunks, cut up potatoes and carrots in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cream of mushroom and chicken soup.
Add 2 cans of water.
Bake in stove at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: regal chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, whip heavy cream to soft peaks.
Combine chicken, celery, grapes, almonds, parsley, salt and mayonnaise with whipped cream, folding well.
Chill.
Just before serving, mound chicken salad in center of a pretty plate lined with fresh lettuce and garnish with more grapes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Peel potatoes.
Boil uncovered in 2 cups water until but 1 cup of fluid remains.
Remove the vegetables.
Stir the liquid until it reaches the boiling point again.
Slowly add white sugar, then add brown sugar.
Once sugar is entirely dissolved, take pan off heat to cool slowly.
Pour in bottle and store several days in dark place before using.
Good.

title: holiday meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except barbecue sauce and roll into balls and fry.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix together biscuit mix and sugar.
In separate bowl combine, egg, milk, vegetable oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry mix and beat lightly until well combined.
Do not over mix as it will result in tough muffins.
Fold in 3/4 - 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips, depending on taste.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes depending on muffin cup size. Makes 12-18 muffins depending on muffin cup size.

title: swiss steak
directions: Beat flour, garlic, salt and pepper into steak.
Place in baking dish.
Add stewed tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add 1 cup of Swiss cheese.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.
Great with garlic bread and green salad.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm water and let stand.
Cream eggs and shortening.
Mix flour, sugar and milk powder.
Add water to egg mixture, then add flour mixture.
When mixed well, put a piece of waxed paper over top of mixing bowl and set a plate on top.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and let set to rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
This makes about 48 rolls.
Bake and store in freezer.
Take out and use as needed. Reheat in oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir in water and Jell-O, until Jell-O is dissolved. Stir in cranberry sauce. Refrigerate until partially set. Fold in sour cream and refrigerate until completely set.

title: summer fruit stack
directions: Break cake into pieces.
Mix remaining items with cake except fruit.
Put layer of cake mixture in bowl.
Put layer of fruit. Continue with layer of cake and layer of fruit.
End with layer of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: ravioli and broccoli salad
directions: Prepare ravioli as directed on package.
Meanwhile, cut broccoli and tomato.
In skillet over high
heat, add 3 tablespoons salad dressing.
Add broccoli
and
stir
until coated. Add 1/4 cup water.
Reduce heat and
cover.
Cook
2 minutes. Uncover and stir-fry 2 mintues.
Drain ravioli, place in large bowl.
Add broccoli, tomato and 1/2
salad
dressing.
Toss to coat.
Spoon
salad
onto platter.
Serve
warm
or
chilled. Sliver slices of Parmesan on top of salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and cream (mix well).
Slowly add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: great depression cake(1929 crash)
directions: In a large saucepan, simmer the first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes,
stirring	occasionally.
Cool 10 minutes.
Blend together
the
remaining
ingredients;
stir into the mixture. Pour
batter
into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool; dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: alabama coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternating with evaporated milk.
Mix in coconut and lemon flavoring.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: easy banana pancakes
directions: Follow instructions for mixing pancakes on Bisquick box. Peel bananas and mash with fork. Stir into pancake mixture and cook. You may substitute other fruits getting "soft" such as strawberries, blueberries and peaches. In the winter, use canned pineapple or peaches sliced into small pieces.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Beat pumpkin, flour, sugar and spice until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat again; add milk and beat until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell and add a meringue topping or Cool Whip.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Toast pecans 10 minutes at 300°.
Combine all ingredients except nuts and vanilla.
Cook.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Cook meat until brown; stir in green beans (drained), soup and seasonings and cook a little longer (5 minutes).
Pour into crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: vegetable wagon wheel
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add garlic, chives and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes. Arrange 2 1/2 packages Brussels sprouts in circle in skillet beginning at outer edge.
Add corn within circle of Brussels sprouts.
Place tomatoes in next circle. Add remaining Brussels sprouts in center of tomatoes.
Pour stock over vegetables.
Cook covered over low heat for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut the hot dogs in half. Remove the crescent rolls and cut each in half. Wrap half a crescent roll around each hot dog half. Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix sweet milk for 1 minute.
Add lemonade and Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended.
Put in graham cracker crust (pie or tarts). Refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, celery, oranges and nuts.
Add sugar and 2 boxes of cherry Jell-O.
Mix all together.
Put in bowl until set.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Beat egg white with salt until soft peaks form.
Add brown sugar in 2 additions, beating lightly after each.
Mixture will be much thinner than for meringue.
Stir in nuts.
Drop, 2-inches apart, from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in very slow oven (250°) about 30 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli with lemon cream
directions: Clean and cook broccoli 8 to 10 minutes. Place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in salad bowl.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour all ingredients into punch bowl.
Mix.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.

title: grandma's spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to low broil with rack in lowest position. Saute spinach and garlic in olive oil.
Cook down until tender. Drain well and place spinach mixture in a bowl.
In a separate bowl beat 3 eggs.
Pour egg mixture over spinach and garlic.
Heat olive oil in oven-proof skillet until semi-hot.
Pour spinach mixture into skillet.
Sprinkle grated parmesan cheese on top.
Place on lowest position and broil until top is browned.
Using pizza cutter, cut through the middle like a pizza into 6 slices. Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks over cherries.
Sift dry cake mix over this.
Cover with melted butter and top with coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake for 1 hour. Serve hot or cold.
Can put whipped cream on top and dot with cherries.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together gently. Butter sides and bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in vegetables.

title: brer rabbit molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 to 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs. Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well; chill.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and 1/4 cup oleo.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, combine sugar, softened oleo, eggs and vanilla; beat.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas and add in a layer.
Add crushed pineapple.
Top with whipped topping; garnish with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh fruit delight
directions: Scoop yogurt into dessert dishes.
Top with marinated strawberries.
Add extra splash of Cointreau if desired.
Garnish with whipped cream dollop.
Enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a baking dish.
Poke holes in the top of the loaf to hold sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; glaze with extra ketchup or tomato sauce and bake for about 15 minutes more or until cooked through.

title: yogurt-tahini dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Makes one cup.

title: spinach and artichoke party dip
directions: Combine sour cream and party dip mix in medium bowl.
Stir in artichokes, spinach and pimentos.
Cut, slice off top of round loaf of bread.
Hollow out center of bread, leaving 1-inch shell. Reserve bread pieces for dipping.
Spoon dip into bread shell. Serve warm or cold.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl. Add eggs, beating well with spoon. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Add nuts. Spread in 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edge. Do not overcook.

title: chicken o'phyllis
directions: Chop chicken in 1-inch pieces.
Roll it in flour, salt and pepper mix.
Brown in oil in skillet.
In a bowl, put celery, pepper and onion.
Melt butter in microwave; add butter and ketchup to chopped veggies.
Put this mixture over top of chicken and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put liquid ingredients in bottom of large coffee maker.
Put dry ingredients in basket and perk.
Makes 36 cups.
You may substitute 2 peach jello.
Apricot is sometimes hard to find.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cake mix) together and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top and drizzle the melted butter over the top and bake in a 325° oven. Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Add chopped pecans or walnuts sprinkled over top and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Preheat
2 inches of oil in deep skillet (375°).
Use a funnel with
a 3/18-inch opening.
Pour 1/2 cup batter in the funnel, holding
finger
over the opening and 1-inch over the oil.
Pour batter in a circular design.
Let it brown and turn only
once. Remove
from
pan and drain.
Serve hot with powdered sugar, brown sugar or maple syrup.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Place corn syrup and sugar into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add rice krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture into 13x9x2 inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Set aside. Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels together in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread evenly over cereal mixture.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into 2 x 1 inch bars when cool.

title: meatball soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo until golden.
Add this to ground pork. Add a little salt.
Mix well.
Make tiny meatballs and roll in crumbs.
Cut up carrots, celery and potatoes.
Add to water; boil. Add salt, dill, parsley, etc.
Then add meatballs when water is boiling.
Cook until meat and vegetables are done.
Let cool down. Mix sour cream, milk and flour in blender.
Add slowly to soup, stirring constantly.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine lightly the beef, crumbs, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf.
Mix other ingredients and pour half over meat loaf.
Baste with remainder after 3/4 hour. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice and peel apples.
Place them into a 10 x 6-inch buttered pan.
Mix the other ingredients until grainy.
Sprinkle the mixture evenly over the apples, then bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sole and crab cardinale
directions: Poach the sole in white wine until white.
Top with crabmeat and your own white sauce.
Add a slice of Swiss cheese and bake to a golden brown.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Add butter, cheese and eggs to hot spaghetti.
Form mixture into "crust" in a 10-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.

title: tim's baked beans
directions: Wash and pick over beans; cover with cold water.
Add soda and soak overnight.
Next morning, rinse beans and parboil in fresh water until skins wrinkle.
Drain off bean water and retain. Place whole onion in bottom of bean pot.
Add beans, maple syrup and mustard.
Score pork and place on top of beans and add bean water; cover.
Cook in slow oven of 325° for 8 hours.
Check periodically and add bean water as needed.
For the last hour, cook uncovered, so pork will brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Hollow out a loaf of pumpernickel or other bread loaf. Save the center bread to slice for dipping. The dip should be mixed and refrigerated a day in advance.

title: savory pork chops en casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper, oregano and breadcrumbs.
Combine applesauce and horseradish; mix well.
Combine tomato mixture, applesauce mixture and sauerkraut.
Pour into covered casserole.
Saute pork chops until golden brown.
Lay chops on sauerkraut mixture and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until chops are tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apple.
Add marshmallows and sugar and mix well.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, fold in whipped cream.
Spoon on pineapple slices and serve.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Carefully stir in potatoes.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: macadamia-pear tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter pie or tart pan.
Combine flour, the 1/2 cup sugar, nuts and baking powder.
Stir well.
Stir together milk, egg and vanilla in small bowl until blended.
Add to flour mixture and stir until smooth.
Place each pear half, cut side down, on cutting board.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Slide spatula under pear to keep it in its original shape and place in buttered pan with stem end facing toward center. Pour batter over pears.
Sprinkle tops of pears with remaining 1 teaspoon sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely on wire rack.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Can be stored in refrigerator for up
to 3 days.
Serves six.
Each serving:
255 calories, 4 g protein, 9 g fat, 40 g carbohydrates, 148 mg sodium, 48 mg cholesterol.

title: cherry nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with cherry juice. Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana bread(2 loaves)
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture and add remaining ingredients. Mix well; pour batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 70 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain the pineapple; reserve juice. Saute pork and onion in a large skillet in hot oil for 10 to 12 minutes or until pork is done. Combine reserved pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and spices.
Stir well.
Add juice mixture and green
pepper to skillet.
Cook over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple and snow peas. Cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy beef bake
directions: In large cast iron skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onions until tender.
Remove onions and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together.
Drain well.
Add cooked onion, mashed potatoes and seasonings.
Stir together; pat down.
Mix biscuit mix and milk together; pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease one 9x5x3-inch loaf pan.
Beat eggs slightly; add butter and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and walnuts.
Stir well and pour into pineapple mixture.
Stir to moisten.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test doneness with a toothpick.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: broccoli bread
directions: In mixer, beat eggs on high until frothy.
Add cornbread mix, salt, peppers, meat and 1/2 stick margarine, while beating these slowly into eggs.
Use microwave on High for 1 minute to heat broccoli and chopped seasoning.
Drain and add to mixture.
Add cheese.

title: sugar-free banana loaf
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir to blend.
Puree the bananas.
Add the bananas and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: easiest cookie recipe in the world
directions: Mix and form into 1-inch balls.
Flatten on cookie sheet to 1/4-inch with a glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Let set on cookie sheet 1 minute before removing to cooling racks.
May frost or leave unfrosted.

title: cheese and bacon frittata(breakfast)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 1/2-inch round pan or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium bowl, with fork or wire whisk or handbeater, beat eggs, milk, onion, butter, salt and pepper until well blended.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon evenly over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until golden brown. Makes 4 servings.
Recommend Corning Ware.

title: rhonda's cookies(double chocolate chip)
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients, then add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 112 cookies (big).

title: 5 minute devil's food cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Then add flour, soda and cocoa; mix well.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° in a tube pan for 40 minutes.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Mix salt in cornmeal, pour on hot water, then add enough cold water to thin mush so it pours slowly out of the bowl.
Add fat. Pour mush by spoonfuls on a hot griddle or skillet.
Turn on both sides to brown.

title: gloop
directions: Pour white glue into clean empty jar.
Add 1/2 cup water and 10 drops food coloring.
Stir.
Combine Borax and 3/4 cup water in plastic bowl.
Slowly pour glue mixture into Borax solution and stir well.
Borax causes mixture to congeal.
Scoop gloop out of water and knead in your hands until dry enough to play with. Store in sealed container.
It will keep for several weeks.
This will dry out after a lot of handling.

title: cherry-peach dumplings
directions: Stir water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves into pie filling in 10-inch skillet.
Add peaches; bring to boil, add cherry pie filling.
Add milk to egg to make 1/2 cup; stir into biscuit mix to form soft dough.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls on top of boiling fruit.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes; cover skillet and cook 10 minutes more.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl the chicken, celery, water chestnuts, rice, Cheddar cheese and green onion.
In small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, soup, salt and lemon juice.
Add this mixture to chicken mixture and stir to combine.
Spoon into a 9 x 13 inch casserole - top with crushed potato chips and sliced almonds. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry slowly to a golden brown in a 3 to 4-quart saucepan.
Add onion and cook slowly, without browning, 5 minutes.
Add corn (including liquid) and potatoes. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Add boiling water and cook slowly until potatoes are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in milk.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pralines
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Bring to boil over medium heat. Boil for about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add pecans and butter. Stir until thick, then drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: okra puffs
directions: Okra may be fresh, frozen or canned.
Boil in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Chop, mash and beat with a fork or in a blender.
Add egg, sugar, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add and beat.
Drop by 1 teaspoon into deep, very hot fat.
Brown, turn without pricking. Cook until very brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 or more.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt, milk and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Pour in plate.
Let cool.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Spread butter on bread.
Fit 6 slices (butter side down) in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup of berries.
Layer with rest of bread and berries.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until brown and cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal as directed on box, then add the frozen broccoli.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
This is very delicious.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add taco mix.
Lay rolls in greased pie pan.
Put hamburger mixture on top and layer tomatoes, olives and sour cream.
Add Cheddar cheese and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Layer beans, hamburger and soup in casserole dish. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buffet mashed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Halve them and scoop out insides.
Rice or grate potatoes into large bowl.
Add cream cheese and beat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spoon filling back into skins.
Reheat for about 20 minutes or until tops are browned slightly.
After filling is put into skins, they may be frozen.

title: french toast casserole
directions: *Or use real maple syrup.

title: curried dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook cabbage, onion, kidney beans and tomatoes. Add browned ground beef. Add salt and cook on low heat 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to the directions.
Put 1/2 of the batter into a Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in oven preheated to 350°.
Melt together the evaporated milk, butter and caramels.
Pour this over baked cake.
Sprinkle with the pecans and chocolate chips.
Spread remaining cake batter over this.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until cake tests done. Enjoy!

title: fluffy apple pancake
directions: Melt margarine. Add 1/2 c. sugar and the water. Bring to a boil, then add the apples and cook 15 minutes. Pour into a heavy pie pan. Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and sugar until smooth. Pour over apples. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, until it puffs up and is golden brown. Serve immediately. Excellent!

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in large pan and cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Remove chicken from water and cool.
Reserve broth for other uses.
Bone chicken and chop into bite size pieces.
Place into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef cubes.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frypan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until brown. Taste meat.
If it is not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to pan; stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: dying sand
directions: You will need paper cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix frozen strawberries, pineapple, pie filling and fruit cocktail in a bowl and chill. The strawberries being slightly frozen still when you serve this makes it very refreshing.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients with a hand beater until desired consistency is reached.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine vanilla wafers with melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until cooled while mixing other ingredients.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Brown Ritz crackers in butter.
Mix all ingredients (except crackers) together in casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers on top. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. This recipe may be halved.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan. Stir together sifted flour, soda, and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, oil, and buttermilk.
Stir to blend.
Stir in bananas and walnuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for one hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix together; place deer strips in mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Pepper meat and cook on grill until bright red, not dry.

title: pork adobo
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and marinate 30 to 60
minutes. In a skillet, simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes until the meat is almost tender.
Remove the stock; stir-fry the pork until it's a little bit brown or well fried, then put back the stock.
Season to taste.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell 5 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate together.
Add sugar and half and half; stir until smooth.
Pour into a bowl and set in cold water, stirring until cool.
Remove bowl from water and beat in eggs and yolk.
Let stand until solid.
Top with whipped cream (optional).

title: black night barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for approximately one hour.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in heavy 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; add sugar and stir until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour.
Crush sugar frosted flakes into medium fine crumbs.
Add to chocolate mixture together with nutmeats; mix well.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Pull biscuits apart,
making
thinner
biscuits
(20 pieces).
Wrap apple quarters in biscuit dough, pinching dough together
around edges.
Place dumplings in 9 x 13-inch pan or large
baking
dish.
Melt	butter; stir in sugar and let dissolve.
Add
water.
Let come to a boil.
Pour over dumplings. Bake
at
350° (covered) for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender. Uncover and bake until golden brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain any grease. Mix seasonings to meat. Mix other ingredients in a large pot without draining. Add meat. Bring to boil and simmer for 1 hour.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large saucepan. Blend in brown sugar and salt. Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Blend in confectioners sugar gradually. Add vanilla. Mix well. Thin with a few drops of cream, if needed.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ruth marshall's chocolate cake
directions: Mix liquid ingredients together first, then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
Use large bowl and put all ingredients together.
Beat until mixed.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until center springs back.

title: amish oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, soak oats, butter and sugar overnight.
Next day, preheat oven to 350°.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.
Make 36 cookies.
This is a chewy cookie.

title: jose supreme breakfast burrito
directions: Smash and refried cooked beans.
While this is done go ahead and add all other ingredients together.
Heat up tortillas and place all ingredients into
tortilla and roll it up into a delicious burrito.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Mix on high until well blended and smooth.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Add topping.
Serve chilled.

title: oatmeal pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine honey, oil and eggs.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until blended. Stir in orange juice, pumpkin and pecans.

title: geneva's pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter until smooth; add eggs one at a time. Add flavoring; beat until mixed well.
Add flour.
Put in a cold oven.
Set oven at 325°.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Test in one hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil.
The longer it boils the thicker it becomes.
May be stored in refrigerator.

title: corn crisped chicken
directions: Dip pieces of chicken in milk.
Roll in mixture of corn flakes and seasoning.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan lined with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until drumstick is tender when pierced with a fork.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Melt chocolate and butter. Set aside. Boil syrup and sugar for 2 minutes and add chocolate mixture. Beat eggs well then slowly add hot mixture to eggs, beating constantly. Add vanilla and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside. In mixing bowl, combine vegetable oil, both sugars, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and combine well. Stir in carrots and nuts. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Allow cake to cool completely before frosting.

title: menudo
directions: Boil your beef tripe about 2 hours.
Add hominy and then add all your spices and cook another 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Add more spices if you need to.
Serve with saltine crackers.
It is great for breakfast or supper on a cold day.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and onion in the microwave for 6 minutes or until done to your taste.
Mix ingredients and let set until cheese melts.
Serve over potato chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook the bacon (crisply), drain, and crumble into small pieces. Using only the florets and the most tender stem sections of the broccoli, chop the broccoli into very tiny pieces.
(The rest of the stems may be saved for soup or discarded.)
Peel the red onion, and chop it very finely.
In a bowl, combine the broccoli, onion, celery, and raisins.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in casserole; melt butter and pour over
mixture.
Put
bread	crumbs	on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil
chicken
in enough water to cover it about 1-inch above chicken.
When
done, remove from broth.
Break noodles into pieces
about
bite size and add to broth.	Cook 15 minutes.
Add other
ingredients and let simmer while you remove chicken	from bones
and	cut
up.
Then add chicken and cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Rinse and drain vegetables.
Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat to melted.
Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly (add garlic if desired).
Boil and stir one minute.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour chicken mixture into pastry lined pan.
Place second pastry on top.
Seal edges and cut slits in top for steam.	Dash salt on top.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cover edges with foil for first 25 minutes then remove for remaining cooking time.

title: fig cookies
directions: Mix together.
Add about 1/4
cup of water to mix dough if needed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Clean and cut squash in slices.
Boil until tender.
Transfer to baking dish in layers of crushed cracker crumbs and bell pepper.
Top with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with pork or venison.

title: sous' american way
directions: In saucepan, stir bean soup until smooth.
Gradually blend in beef broth, water and sherry.
Heat, stirring occasionally. Garnish with "dollop" of sour cream or lemon slice (thin).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and cook over medium heat until thick. Pour over fresh strawberries.

title: hamburger cook-up
directions: Combine the two ingredients.
Form patties.
Cook thoroughly on hot grill or fry in hot pan.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple pecan cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs and pineapple well.
Add pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 11 inch pan at 350° for approximately 40-45 minutes.
(Do not oil or grease pan.)
Cool completely before frosting.

title: meatball stew(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; form into balls.
Cook and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add meatballs.
Bring to a boil, then simmer about 20 minutes until veggies are done.
More water may be needed to cover meatballs and vegetables.
Thicken with cornstarch or flour, whichever you prefer.
May be served over rice or as is.

title: white sangria
directions: Combine the lemon, orange and lime slices and sugar in a large pitcher, stirring with a wooden spoon until sugar dissolves.
Stir in brandy and wine.
Chill.
Add club soda (and ice cubes if you wish) just before serving.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: meringue teasers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cover cookie sheets with aluminum foil; beat egg whites in small bowl until foamy. Gradually beat in sugar until meringue forms stiff peaks. Add vanilla and salt. Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts. Drop by teaspoons onto prepared sheets. Garnish each with chocolate chip.

title: teeala
directions: Put oil in pot and fry.
Add onion, sliced.
Fry until half done.
Get a casserole dish and put 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce and 3 tablespoons grated cheese and bread crumbs in.
Layer vegetables, sauce, cheese and bread crumbs.
Add small amount of oregano, parsley, garlic and basil between layers.
Cover with foil and seal good.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or 1 hour until potatoes are done.

title: butterhorns
directions: In
a large bowl combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter as
for
a
pie
crust,
set aside.
Dissolve yeast in water. Add
with
the
milk
to
the flour mixture, mix well. Cover
and refrigerate
overnight.
The next day divide dough into
four equal parts.
On a lightly floured board roll each portion into a 12-inch circle.
Brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter
and
cut into 12 pie shaped wedges.
Roll up beginning with
wide
end. Place
on a greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Yields 48 rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, eggs and onion.
Layer broccoli with 1 cup soup mixture and 1 cup cheese cracker crumbs.
Repeat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Poke holes in cake.
Pour Kahlua over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cola salad
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Sprinkle gelatin into cream cheese.
Heat cola to boiling and pour over mixture.
Mix; add nuts and put into mold.
Let sit for 1 to 2 hours before refrigerating.
Salad separates, 3 layers.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In mixing bowl on medium speed, beat cream cheese and brown sugar 2 minutes or until smooth. Add sour cream, vanilla, lemon, cinnamon, milk and pudding mix, beating 1 minute or until blended. Chill 1 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place balls, sugar side up, 3 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tuna pitas
directions: Combine tuna, cheese, mayonnaise and onion (if desired) according to taste.
Slice pita bread in half and fill with tuna mixture.
Microwave on High for 20 to 45 seconds.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes; run through colander.
Cook celery, onions and banana pepper together.
Make a paste with some of the cooled tomato paste and the flour.
Bring all of the ingredients to a slow boil and cook 30 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars; seal.
Put jars in a hot water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 quarts.

title: everybody's beef burgundy(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix in a 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Bake in tightly foil-covered casserole for 5 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice or toast or what-have-you.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add to squash the egg, milk, melted butter, onion, sugar and dry crumbs.
Put thin layer in a greased quart size baking dish. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy fudge recipe
directions: Mix in saucepan all ingredients (except chips, vanilla and nuts) while stirring constantly and heat to boiling for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups chips and vanilla and nuts last.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: nectar berry cobbler
directions: Mix first three items lightly in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Blend well last four items.
Cover berries with topping and bake in moderate oven (350°) until crust is brown.

title: mary jane pita snacks
directions: Chop fine and mix all.
Break large pita bread into pieces. Cover with mix and broil 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
(Cook the bacon first.)

title: chicken tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large nonstick skillet, heat oil; add pepper, onions and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, 2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Add chicken; cook, breaking up chicken with back of wooden spoon until no longer pink.
Stir in cumin and coriander; cook 1 minute.
Add salsa, cilantro and chili powder; cook, partially covered, 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer, until mixture is thick but not dry.
Arrange tacos on baking sheet; bake 6 to 8 minutes until crisp.
To serve, divide chicken mixture evenly among taco shells.
Top with lettuce, sour cream, cheese and olives.

title: luscious lime angel squares
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Refrigerate until mixture just begins to thicken, about 35 minutes. Place cake cubes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish coated with nonstick cooking spray; set aside. In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Beat in sugar and lemon juice. Add gelatin mixture; beat until combined. Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping. Spread over cake, covering completely. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, until firm. Cut into squares; top with remaining whipped topping.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine sugar and flour; place on a shallow plate.
Dip both sides of each tomato slice into the mixture.
Combine the egg and milk.
Dip each tomato slice, then dip into the bread crumbs.
In a skillet, heat butter and oil over medium-high.
Fry tomatoes until brown on both sides but firm enough to hold their shape.

title: easy green bean casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, cook green beans according to the package microwave directions.
Drain beans.
In the 1-quart casserole, stir together mushroom soup, sour cream and pimiento. Stir in beans.
Cook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 4 to 6 minutes or until bubbly, stirring twice.
Sprinkle French fried onions atop.
Makes 4 servings.

title: saltine cracker candy
directions: Add sugar to milk.
Mix and boil three minutes; take off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, butter and crushed saltines.
Fold in pecans.
Drop out of spoon onto wax paper.

title: soda crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
In a bowl, combine flour with salt and baking soda.
With a pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk;
mix well.
Turn dough onto a floured board and form into a ball.
Knead lightly.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut dough into 50 (2-inch) squares; prick each cracker with a fork 2 or 3 times.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries, using food grinder, food processor or blender.
Measure cranberries and cover with equal amount of sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Then drain juice from cranberries. Add celery, pecans, marshmallows and grapes.
Beat whipping cream with electric mixer until very stiff.
Sweeten to taste and fold into cranberry mix.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put tuna in the bottom of a casserole dish, then potato chips and last the mushroom soup.
Repeat in layers.
Cut a few slices of cheese on top of soup.
Put in oven and brown a little.

title: instant chocolate mix
directions: Use three (3) heaping tablespoons per cup.

title: summer stir-fry
directions: Slice zucchini and squash into 1/8-inch rounds.
Chop tomatoes.
Slice onion and separate into rings.
Heat the olive oil in a hot wok.
Add onion, zucchini and squash.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and oregano.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until tomatoes are warm.
Pour into microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and microwave on low until cheese begins to melt.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix meal, soda, eggs, milk, salt, oil and corn.
Mix well.
Pour half mixture in hot, greased iron skillet; then layer beef, Ro-Tel and then cheese.
Pour remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add eggs and milk.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Place in a cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Melt butter in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Add stuffing. Layer 1/2 the chicken, then the package of broccoli, the rest of the chicken and the cheese.
Mix cream of celery soup with broth and pour over top of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef olive spread
directions: Mix sherry and minced onion.
Let stand.
Mix softened cream cheese with rest of ingredients.
Fold in sherry/onion mixture. Best when prepared early in day.
Serve with rye crackers.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix butter, 4 tablespoons sugar and graham cracker crumbs in spring-form pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, 1 cup sugar and vanilla with beater.
Fold in sour cream.
Put in crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave in 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes or more before removing.

title: spinach squares
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Add spinach and rice and mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Cut into squares for serving. (Can be prepared a day ahead.)

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: yo kan
directions: Rinse kanten and soak in 5 cups of water for 5 minutes. Cook until
it
starts to boil; add sugar and continue cooking for about
minutes,	stirring
constantly.
Add
the "An", mixing well
and
continue
cooking
for 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into
a
9 x	13-inch
container.
Cool and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into desired shapes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Soak tortillas in broth until soft.
Saute onions and celery in broth until tender.
Line a baking dish with softened tortillas.
Mix together celery, onion, salt, pepper, soups and tomatoes.
Alternate layers of chicken, soup mixture and cheese. Cover and cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix everything well in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased glass lasagna pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Uncover and let brown a little, about another 15 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese muffins
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add cheese soup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Add Bisquick mix and stir well.
Pour batter into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes.

title: zesty marinated vegetables
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large shallow dish.
Combine water, vinegar and dressing mix in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over vegetables, tossing lightly to coat.
Cover and chill overnight.
Yield:
8 servings (about 33 calories per serving).

title: frijoles and greens
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain off half the fat.
Add chopped greens to same pan.
Add beans and bacon and simmer until hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Take juice from pineapple; pour in casserole dish with sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add pineapple chunks and cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers (1 1/2 packs).
Pour over pineapple.
Put 6 to 8 pats of butter on top.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: sally lunn(an old recipe)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Beat egg well; add to shortening and sugar.
Add flour and milk, alternately, making a smooth batter.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: In a medium bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water and pineapple juice.
Stir in grapes, pineapple, walnuts and celery and refrigerate until the mixture has thickened to the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in the cranberry sauce and spoon into a 12-cup mold.
Chill.
Yields 12 servings.

title: saucy skillet fish
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add fish and shake to coat (if using fillets, cut into serving-size pieces first).
In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender; remove and set aside.
Add fish to the skillet; cook over medium heat for 3-5 minutes on each side or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch.
Place cheese, ham and onion on bottom of pie shell.
Pour egg mixture evenly over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes after removing from oven before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Bake at 450° in a well-oiled hot black skillet.
Be sure the skillet is hot so that the batter sizzles when poured in.
Bake until golden brown and when thumped, sounds hollow.

title: clam casserole(serves 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in
a greased casserole for 45 minutes at 325°.
Pour a can of heated mushroom soup, undiluted, over clam dish.

title: turnip salad
directions: *Other root vegetables may be used: kohlrabi or rutabaga.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line large casserole dish with tortillas.
Brown ground beef. Add salt, onion and chili powder.
Cook until onions are clear. Put meat on top of tortillas; cover with beans and 1/2 of the cheese.
Add another layer of tortillas.
Mix mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes with chilies together and pour over top of tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese and cover.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Cook broccoli, drain well and set aside.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add soup, mushrooms, cheese spread and hot sauce.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir in broccoli and salt. Serve in chafing dish or mini crock-pot.
Great with corn chips or Melba toast squares.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Cook 4 pieces of chicken in 4 cups water until tender.
Cook 1 box of mixed frozen vegetables until soft, about 10 minutes. Clean, shell and devein shrimp and set aside until later.

title: kulfi(indian ice cream)
directions: Coarsely grind almonds and pistachios.
Remove the skin of the cardamom and powder it in a spice mill.
In a mixing bowl, mix the two cans of evaporated milk and condensed milk.
Mix in half of the nut mixture and cardamom powder.
Mix well until the condensed milk dissolves into the evaporated milk.
Transfer the mixture into a plastic container with a lid.
Freeze the mixture until the ice cream has set.
Remove the container about 10 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle rest of the nut mixture.
Cut the ice cream into squares or scoop with an ice cream scoop.
(The nut mixture can be sprinkled after portioning into individual plates.)

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: Prepare stewed chicken. When chicken is tender, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Combine milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Stir just to moisten. Drop from tablespoon directly onto chicken in boiling stock. Reduce heat (don't lift cover). Simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until done. Remove dumplings and chicken to hot platter. Keep hot while preparing Chicken Gravy.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet with 2 tbsp. oil. Drain liquid after browning. Add potatoes, cut into quarters, onion, slice in rings, and can of green beans with liquid. Cover all with lid and cook on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes. Pork chops and potatoes should be tender.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all together in Dutch oven. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: rice krispies wonder fudge
directions: Melt chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and corn syrup.
Mix.
Add vanilla and sugar. Mix.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix lightly, spread in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Let harden, cut in squares.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions. Drain. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, processed cheese spread, Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and eggs in 3-quart casserole. Add cooked macaroni. Fold in thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 16 servings.

title: richard's ranger cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder together. Add to creamed mixture thoroughly. Add vanilla.
Add oatmeal and corn flakes until moist. Drop by tablespoons on slightly greased cookie sheet, about 12 cookies to each pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen total.

title: corn fritters
directions: Spoon in hot grease. Cook until golden brown.

title: microwave mexican stuff
directions: Layer in a microwave dish. Spread cream cheese in the bottom of the dish. Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Layer grated cheese on top of chili. Spread chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes on top of the cheese. Microwave until bubbly.
Serve with chips.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add the rest of the ingredients. (Batter will be fairly stiff.)
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Roll out on floured board about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into any shape you desire and bake at 350° on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Check after 8 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: orange cool whip salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add all fruit immediately. Mix well and pour into shallow dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook onion in heated oil in large frying pan over medium heat until soft.
Add garlic; cook, stirring, about 1 minute.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add clam liquid to onion mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock. Stir.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high for 4 hours. This can also be cooked on the stove.

title: bee's chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 items together and put in a casserole dish.
Top with soup.
Place in a 300° oven and bake for 30 minutes.
The last 5 or 10 minutes, sprinkle crushed chips on top of casserole and finish baking.

title: no sugar cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Mix all the dry ingredients together, then add the raisins and applesauce.
Bake in a loaf or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine butter, sugar and peanut butter in large bowl. Beat in eggs and vanilla. In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda and baking powder. Mix into creamed mixture at low speed. Stir in one at a time, rice cereal, nuts, oats, chocolate chips and coconut with a spoon. Drop by tablespoons 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes or until set. Remove immediately.

title: microwave pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and spices in a glass dish.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Stir and cover.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 pints.

title: orange charlotte
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Add sugar, lemon juice, orange juice and pulp.
Chill in pan of ice water.
When quite cold and thick, whip until frosty.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream gently.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients together and put a tablespoon of mixture in the center of open crescent roll.
Roll up and seal. Bake until brown.
Drizzle nacho cheese sauce over top and serve.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and soda.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with 1/2 cup lemonade concentrate.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8
minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Brush hot cookies lightly with remaining concentrate.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: jean's vegetable soup
directions: Put hamburger in 6-quart pan. Add half full of water. Start cooking. Add everything else; cook 6 hours. (If pan is not full, add water until it is.)

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Store in tightly covered container.
Three-fourth cup makes about 15 (6 ounce) servings.

title: spicy red beans
directions: Cover beans with hot water and let soak overnight.
Next morning, add all other ingredients, except for hot sauce and liquid crab boil, to beans.
Let come to full boil for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to low and cook for 30 minutes.
Then add hot sauce and liquid crab boil.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg with spoon and spread in pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inches.
Next, mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese
with mixer and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in oil; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Place dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add beaten egg and fruit
cocktail
with
juice;
mix	together.
Put into a medium size pan that has been greased well.
Sprinkle on top: chopped walnuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine in water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add flour, using electric mixer.
Mixture will be thick and pull away from the sides.
Let cool 2 minutes, then add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for another 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not open oven while baking.
After time is up, turn off oven, open door slightly and leave pastry in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
This allows pastry to dry out.
Let cool completely before filling.
Fill with Cream Puff Filling.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Makes a stiff batter.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thoroughly mix instant vanilla pudding and pineapple tidbits together in bowl.
Stir until it thickens.
Drain your mandarin oranges and fruit cocktail, then fold in.
Add your Tang.
Stir thoroughly.
Then add your banana and frozen strawberry slices. Mix altogether.
Serve chilled.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: For each serving, spread dressing and salsa on tortilla; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat.
Roll up.
Wrap each tortilla in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: chef salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour favorite salad over and enjoy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Let all fruit that are canned drain well.
Mix with other fruits and nuts.
Add whipped cream just before serving.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix fruit.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle in jello and stir.
Chill.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add undrained pineapple, cooking oil, vanilla, eggs and bananas, mixing well, but do not beat.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cut in the shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and milk all at once.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll out to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with floured cutter.
Place on wax paper on a baking sheet.
Place in freezer until frozen solid.
Store frozen biscuits in a plastic freezer bag.

title: sausage cheese casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put bread on bottom, next the cheese and then sausage.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk; pour over casserole.
Mix 1/2 cup milk, mustard and soup together and pour over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Put in cold oven; turn to 300° and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and bake for 30 to 45 minutes longer.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Roll the finished ball in pecans.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk, butter and vanilla in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Fluff.
Stir until melted and mixed well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Makes 5 pounds.

title: artichoke bread
directions: Melt butter, garlic and sesame seed.
Add bread chunks from middle of bread.
Fry until brown.
Mix sour cream, cheese, Parmesan, parsley and lemon pepper.
Stir in drained artichoke hearts and toast mixture.
Spoon in bread and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into ball and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in a jello ring or bundt pan, that is sprayed with pam. Serve with strawberry preserves and crackers.

title: easy pigs-in-the-blanket
directions: Wrap each wiener in an individual biscuit, pinching the edges together.
Bake according to the directions on the can.
Great to dip in mustard or ketchup.
The kids will love to help with these.

title: red lollipops
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook until hard-crack stage (300° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; stir in butter and dash of salt.
Cool until slightly thick. Place 15 wooden skewers 5 inches apart on greased baking sheets. Quickly drop sugar mixture from tablespoon over skewers to form lollipops 3 inches in diameter.
Make faces with candy circles. Makes 15 lollipops.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Cut up banana and freeze.
Drain pineapple and freeze. Combine cream, vanilla, banana and pineapple in blender for 3 to 5 minutes on medium to high speed.
Makes a soft ice cream.
Serve or refreeze.

title: cabbage-sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Put cabbage, soup and mustard on top.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
May have to add 2 to 3 tablespoons water. A bit more mustard may be added.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine until golden.
Add beef broth and water.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add sherry and stir 1 minute. Pour into individual bowls.
Top with bread cubes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Broil for 1 minute until cheese melts.

title: italian rum cake
directions: Spread one layer of toast on bottom of spring-form pan. (Crumble some and put in spaces.)
Pour 1/2 of mixture of boiling water and rum into pan.
Pour in cooked chocolate.
Spread another layer of toast.
Pour rest of boiling water and rum in.
Pour in vanilla pudding.
Keep in refrigerator for at least 2 days, covered.
After 2 days, take out of pan and ice with Cool Whip.

title: hazelnut roll
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites, add sugar to egg whites, then add egg yolks, extracts and nuts.
Mix on low speed.
Grease pan.
Add wax paper and grease again.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Put out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Take off wax paper and roll in towel until cool.
Spread with sweetened whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Roll lengthwise twice and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: diabetic cocoa cake
directions: Combine all in mixing bowl.
Beat to blend thoroughly.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan which has been sprayed with Pam and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute chicken until skin is golden. Remove and put in baking dish.
In same skillet, saute onion, green pepper, tomatoes, garlic and bay leaf for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Add broth, rice, saffron and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle or garnish with peas, pimentos and asparagus tips. Serves 4.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions, covered, in butter about 20 minutes.
Add broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Put soup in ovenproof bowls.
Put on bread and cheese.
Broil until melted and light brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from bones.
Layer the chicken in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Slice cheese on top of chicken.
Combine soups and tomatoes.
Add in half bag of Doritos, crumbled.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Place more Doritos on top of everything.
Pour about 1/2 cup of chicken broth over everything.
