Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a skillet, cook mushrooms and onions in margarine until onions are tender. Blend in soup.
Add milk, cheese, garlic salt and poultry seasoning.
Mix half the gravy mix with the spaghetti and pour in casserole dish. Add chopped chicken to remaining gravy mix and pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: reunion apples
directions: Place apples in large cake pan or small roaster. Sprinkle sugar mixed with spices over apples. Dot margarine over top. Pour water over all. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until apples are tender.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Put potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and water in a large frypan and bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add cream, butter and cheese.
Mix lightly and cook uncovered about 10 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs and serve.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrot.
Heat to boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add spaghetti.
Heat through.

title: hashed brown casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine in large kettle:
cucumbers, onions,
green sweet peppers, red sweet peppers, celery.
Mix 4 cups cold water with 1/2 cup pickling salt and pour over above.
Let stand about 2 hours.
Then drain and rinse and mix with the following ingredients that have been brought to a boiling point:
1 1/2 c. brown sugar, 1 1/2 c. white sugar, 3 c. vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric and cloves.
Bring back to boil.
Cook until cucumber slices are tender, about 15 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: crusty basil loaf
directions: In a small bowl, combine margarine and basil; blend well. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours to blend flavors.
Heat grill. Slice loaf into 1-inch slices. Spread with herb-margarine mixture. Arrange slices into loaf shape; wrap securely with foil.
(If loaf is too long for grill, divide in half and wrap each half separately in foil.) When ready to barbecue, place loaf on gas grill over medium coals.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes until margarine is melted and bread is hot, turning occasionally.

title: daisy's lemon pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg yolk and lemon extract. Mix in the dry ingredients with the buttermilk.
After this is well mixed,
fold
in
egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable dinner
directions: Brown chicken.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes; stir until dissolved.
Add vegetables.
Be sure vegetables are covered with water.
Add seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Cover pan; cook on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be served alone or with rice.

title: new year's eve dip
directions: Mix Ranch dressing and sour cream.
Add desired amount of bacon bits and grated cheese.
Chill and serve with potato chips.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve both jellos in 4 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Add well drained pineapple (reserve 1 cup of the juice). Add bananas, 1 tablespoon juice and marshmallows.
Put in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Let set until firm.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 2 heaping teaspoons into tea cup.
Fill with boiling water.
Tea may also be served iced. Keep tea mixture in covered jar.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Mix first eight ingredients with hands thoroughly.
Form into loaf on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown the meat in a frying pan with the vegetable oil and chopped onion.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, water and chili sauce (put into big pot).
Simmer for hours until tender (at least 2 hours).
Add water as needed.
The longer, the better.

title: melanie's favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add dry ingredients to liquid.
Beat until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.
These are delicious!

title: cheese soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery and onion; add broth. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are done. Combine milk, flour, paprika and salt; stir into broth mixture. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese, stirring until melted.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese.
Stir in butter and half and half over low heat.
Pour over potatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Let stand 1 hour or longer.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Chill.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Can be dropped instead of rolled.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix butter, onions, salt, cheese, broccoli and eggs. Stir in muffin mix. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Cut in serving size squares.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnuts with bacon; insert toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Drain fat.
Combine ketchup, sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over top and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls.
Combine chopped chicken and cheese.
Reserve about half of the mixture for use in the sauce.
Place about 3 tablespoons of remaining chicken-cheese mixture on each individual roll, then roll up.
Place roll-ups, seam side down (points down), in a lightly greased 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together; add pimiento, if desired.
Pour over roll-ups and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Cook vegetables in enough water to keep from sticking, until tender.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Spread nuts on bottom. Sprinkle coconut on top of nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jiffy chicken 'n rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
To hot rice in saucepan add cheese spread, milk, chicken, peas and 1/2 can onions.
Stir well. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Beat egg with fork and add with milk to dry mixture.
Knead lightly.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough thin.
Fill with dry cooked fruits or cooked chocolate pudding.
Chill pudding.
Put 1 tablespoon per pie.
Fry in oil until brown, turning once.
Yummy for your tummy!

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Let cool and pour over chopped cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
(Better when sets overnight; can pour off some sauce then.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: won ton soup
directions: Bring the chicken broth to a boil and add the won tons. Turn down and simmer approximately 20 minutes, stirring gently so the won tons don't
stick,
but
be
careful not to rip the skins. When done, add into individual bowls and sprinkle with green onion.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan; spoon cherry filling on top.
Sift cake mix on top of cherries.
Cut oleo very thin; place on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 16 servings.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in confectioners sugar on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
When cool, roll cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight, then serve.

title: blueberry or cherry tart
directions: Cut margarine into flour in large bowl until crumbly.
Add brown sugar and pecans, mixing well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Blend seasonings.
Melt
butter;
add
milk
or
cream. Blend in flour,
stirring
constantly
until smooth and thick. Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour
over mushrooms.	Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes, stir in 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon. Beat egg and beat into milk.
Stir into sweet potato mixture gradually.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with remaining brown sugar.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: While browning meat, add all ingredients and other seasonings (optional).
After meat is brown, drain any excess liquid.
Put 2 tablespoons of mix on wrap (fold in opposite corners, then roll). Wet tip of corner (with water) to close.
Deep-fry until lightly or golden brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix the tomatoes with salt.
Cover and let stand overnight. Wash in cold water and drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients in pot with tomatoes.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Leave 1/8 inch headspace and seal.
Place in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: homemakers wonder salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cherry pie filling, Eagle Brand milk, drained crushed pineapple and nuts. Chill or can be frozen.

title: spinach and rice soup
directions: Bring broth and spinach to boil in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Season with pepper and nutmeg; sprinkle with cheese.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and toss with apples.
Pour into a large pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until almost tender, about 7 minutes.
Place in an 8-inch round baking dish.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine and mix lightly.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Add soda to other 1/2 cup buttermilk, then add to mixture.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add orange slices (cut up) and nuts.
Blend with other ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: red cabbage
directions: Saute onions, bacon and margarine.
Add sugar and continue cooking until onions are golden.
Add apples and wine; bring to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except potato.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in potato; cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: apple chops
directions: Brown chops in pan.
Peel and slice apples.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and raisins with apples.
Grease a baking pan with butter.
Layer apple mixture in baking pan.
Top with chops. Cover with remainder of apple mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender.
Serves 4.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to the directions.
Pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together both sugars, peanut butter, vanilla and 1/2 cup of the melted butter.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.

Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy. Gradually add sugars. Beat until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs. Add oats and mix well. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.

title: stir-fry shrimp
directions: Marinate shrimp in a plastic bowl with some wine and sugar (1 teaspoon or less) for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Heat pan or wok on high with 2 to 3 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Put in scallions and ginger.
Saute for 1 minute until fragrant.
Put in shrimp and saute until pink, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add salt.
Don't overcook.

title: bean medley
directions: Place all ingredients in pan and heat on stove until heated through or place in ovenproof casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees until bubbly and thickened.

title: chocolate sandwich gobs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, margarine and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together cocoa, flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Add baking soda.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie rack.
Form sandwiches by placing icing between 2 cookies.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt, mustard, vinegar and oil on medium in blender. Add minced onion and poppy seed.
Make
a few days ahead. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: baked oysters
directions: Brush the insides of 6 scallop shells or small ramekins with melted butter.
Mix together the tomatoes, parsley, chives, bread crumbs and black pepper.
Place a tablespoon of this mixture on the bottom of each shell.
Lay 4 oysters in each shell and top with a little more of the mixture.
Add a dash
of cream and bake in
a hot oven for 5 to 7 minutes, making sure not to overcook.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Break cake in small pieces and put half in a punch bowl.
Pour pineapple over cake.
Fix pudding mix as directed on box and put half of it in the punch bowl and top with half of the Cool Whip.
Put remaining cake in the bowl; cover with pie filling, then pudding mix and cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Make a brine of 1 cup salt and 5 quarts water.
Soak overnight.
Drain; pour brine off.
Take vinegar, sugar, onions, celery seed and turmeric and bring to a boil.
Put cucumbers in jars (sterilized); pour the mixture over the top of the cucumbers and seal.
Ready in 4 weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onion, pepper and celery.
Combine with vegetables, rice, soup, evaporated milk and cheese.
Mix and put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: greek style lamb with potatoes
directions: Make 3 or 4 incisions in lamb and insert slivers of garlic. Arrange onion rounds on bottom of roasting pan.
Place leg of lamb on top of onions.
Peel potatoes and arrange around lamb.
Pour tomato sauce over everything and sprinkle with spices.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Arrange green beans (May add potatoes, now instead of before) and add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and bake for another hour.
(Time depending on size of leg of lamb.)

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, vanilla and butter in a large pot. Bring to a hard boil.
Test by dropping mixture in cool water. When it forms a soft firm ball take off heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: low-fat chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the onion and green pepper in 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Add beans, tomato paste and tomatoes. Stir in chili powder, salt (if desired), pepper, browned turkey and remaining water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: big doug's 6 alarm chili(super bowl)
directions: Brown meat, onions, garlic, peppers, green chilies, Tabasco sauce and spices.
Cook 1 hour, then add tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer 1 more hour, stirring often.
Then set out in snow bank overnight.
Start again next day on low simmer.
Damn good chili; famous from South Dakota to Florida.
Enjoy.

title: faye's number 7 pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil and buttermilk, mixing well.
Add the dry ingredients and just stir until mixed, but do not beat.
Have non-stick skillet heated to pancake temperature; pour about 1/4 cup batter onto skillet.
Let pancakes begin to bubble on top, and then turn over.
Serve with favorite syrup or preserves.
Makes 12 pancakes.
(Seven ingredients, thus the name.)

title: easy praline bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange crackers in a single layer in an ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).

title: soupe a loignon maison(homemade french onion soup)
directions: Melt butter with oil in a 4-quart saucepan. Add sliced onions and stir.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 15 to 20 minutes until onions are brown.
Uncover.
Raise heat to medium-high. Add salt and sugar.
Cook for 30 minutes or until brown. Turn to medium and stir in flour.
Brown again for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put in a cup of hot bouillon the wine, bay leaf and sage.
Bring to a simmer and continue to simmer slowly for 30 to 40 minutes. Season to taste.
Add croutons or rye bread.
Gob it up with loads of grated Swiss, Parmesan or Mozzarella cheese and pig out!

title: one way cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Drain cherries.
Set aside and reserve juice.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk.
Pour onto the melted butter, but do not stir.
Spoon cherries on top of mixture, then sprinkle with 1/2 cup reserved juice. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden. Serve warm or cold.

title: brotchen(german dinner rolls)
directions: Pour 2 1/2 cups flour into a large bowl and form a well in the center.
In a separate container, mix yeast, sugar and 2 Tbsp. of water (the water comes from the 1 Cup listed above).
Pour the yeast mixture into the well but do not mix with flour at this time.
Cover the bowl with a cloth and set it in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining water and oil and beat until mixed. Turn dough out on counter top and knead until smooth.
Add remaining 1/2 Cup flour as needed.
Put dough in a bowl, cover, and let rise until double in size.
Punch down dough and divide the dough into 12 parts.
Shape into oval rolls and place 3 inches apart on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Use knife to make an X across each roll. Beat egg white and 1 tsp. water with a fork until frothy and brush on the rolls.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and cook.
Defrost broccoli and cut into bite-sizes.
Save flower tops in a separate bowl for later.
In a bowl, mix together mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup, chicken, lemon juice and curry powder.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place broccoli on bottom; add chicken mixture next.
Add cheese on top. (Optional:
Add bits of Macadamia nuts on top.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, put broccoli flowerets around edge of casserole and bake 5 minutes more.

title: apple crisp with macadamia nuts
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl; stir well. Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal; set aside.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the oleo, eggs and water.	Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake	in
a
350° for 6 minutes on the lower oven shelf and 6 minutes on the upper oven shelf.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.

title: cinnamon applesauce
directions: Cut apples in chunks.
Place all ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a low setting.
Simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Mash or cool and puree in food processor. Stores well in glass jars in refrigerator.
Yields approximately 4 cups.

title: jailhouse biscuits
directions: Pass bread and water.

title: dandelion salad
directions: Wash and dry dandelions.
Place in bowl and let stand in a warm place.
Fry and dice bacon.
Drop the bacon with drippings on top of the dandelions.
Mix butter and cream and melt slowly. Beat the eggs; add salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Pour into the frying pan and cook until it thickens like a custard.
Pour this smoking hot over dandelions and stir well.

title: health cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; beat with electric mixer until blended.
Add sugars and mix well.

title: gramma ritchey's fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses; mix well.
Add fruits, nuts, dates, vanilla, soda, water, then flour, spices and salt which have been sifted together.
Drop by spoonful onto well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly and sugar, salt and milk.
Pour mixture into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool pie on wire rack.
Refrigerate covered.
Chill well before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Put brisket in baking pan.
Cover with cranberries, then onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil or pan cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Slice when cool and return to pan.
Add water to pan, if necessary, to thin gravy.
Reheat in gravy.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until juice is absorbed.

title: aunt lynn's veggie soup
directions: In 6 quarts of water, cook bones, onion, celery and salt until tender.
Peel off meat from bones.
Discard bones (or give to your dog).
Add shredded cabbage, tomatoes, basil, pepper, parsley and garlic.
Cook until cabbage is tender, adding water as necessary (about 1 hour).
Add veggies; cook until tender.
Enjoy!

title: apples stuffed with mincemeat
directions: Wash and core apples.
Place in baking dish.
Put 1 tablespoon sugar in each.
Fill centers with mincemeat to which rum or bourbon has been added.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; add remaining sugar and water.
Add lemon and bake 1 hour at 400° until tender.
Serve as a side dish or top with sweetened bourbon-flavored whipped cream and use as dessert.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker and butter.
Crumble crackers into butter; put 1/2 of cracker mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top; pour soup mixture over chicken, then top with remaining 1/2 of crackers.
Cook at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: santa's whiskers(cookies)
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, candied cherries and nuts.
Form into 2 rolls, 2 inches in diameter and 8 inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until edges are golden.

title: sausage brunch bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Combine eggs, milk, bread cubes, cheese, mustard, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Add sausage and pour into greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until nearly set in center.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: quick tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna and set aside 2 tablespoons of tuna juice.
Mix tuna, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to tuna juice; stir into tuna mixture.
Form into small patties.
Fry patties in oil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Turn patties once while frying.
Place patties on several paper towels to drain.

title: roast cornish hen
directions: Coat both inside and outside of Cornish hen with extra virgin olive oil.
Apply salt, pepper and chili powder inside and outside.
Roast on roasting rack (especially for birds) or roasting pan with rack for 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.
To check doneness, remove a leg, making certain clear liquid runs out.
The more hens cooked, the more roasting time is increased.
These birds are crispy and delicious!

title: oatmeal raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine milk, cereal, oatmeal and honey.
Let stand 2 minutes. Add applesauce and egg whites; beat with mixer.
Stir in raisins, then gently fold in dry ingredients.
Put in muffin cups.
Makes 9 muffins.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 14 minutes.

title: beef and gravy noodles
directions: Brown roast on both sides.
Add mushroom soup and 2 cans of water.
Cook over low heat 3 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles.
Cut roast in pieces.
Pour beef and gravy over noodles.

title: roast beef wraps
directions: Mix cream cheese with barbecue sauce. Spread over tortillas. Layer lettuce leaves. Layer roast beef. Sprinkle cheese. Top with tomatoes and onion. Roll up and serve.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add salt, black pepper, sauces and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat 15 minutes.

title: tuna quickie casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water for about 2 minutes. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for about 10 minutes.

title: cheddar-chicken soup
directions: In 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot; add onion, celery and carrot and saute until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle vegetables with flour and stir quickly to combine; gradually stir in water.
Add broth mix and, stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Add asparagus and cook, stirring, for about 3 minutes; add milk and cheese and continue stirring and cooking until cheese melts.
Reduce heat to low, add remaining ingredients, and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, butter, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moistened. Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except topping by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until brown.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, sugar, nuts and cocoa.
Add syrup and bourbon.
Mix real well.
The mixture should be moist but not soggy.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar or granulated sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Balls can be made as far ahead as you like.

title: clam or oyster fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add clam liquor, milk and eggs.
Stir until well blended and add clams and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop from a spoon into deep hot fat (375°) and fry 4 to 6 minutes until well browned.
Drain on unglazed paper.

title: magic rocks
directions: Over the charcoal, pour 1 spoonful water, 1 spoonful ammonia, 1 spoonful blueing and 1 spoonful salt.
Add few drops of food coloring.
Set it in a warm place to grow.

title: ham and cheese calzones
directions: In saucepan, combine spinach and onion; cook according to spinach package directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
Combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, butter or margarine and garlic powder.
Add spinach mixture and muffin mix; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Cover and chill until serving time.
(Or place in a freezer container; seal, label and freeze.) To serve, place chilled or frozen puffs on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.
Bake chilled puffs for 10 to 12 minutes; bake frozen puffs for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 60.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil fryer in large pot full of water.
Save chicken broth. Debone chicken.
Cook egg noodles in broth.
When draining egg noodles, save chicken broth.
Saute celery, onion, pimentos, olives and mushrooms in 1 stick oleo.
Add jar of Cheez Whiz to drained noodles.
Mix chicken, noodles, vegetables and cream of mushroom soup.
Add some chicken broth if mixture is too thick. Heat through before serving.

title: california walnut pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour in a saucepan.
Mix together eggs and vanilla.
Add butter and salt.
Add corn syrup and walnut pieces.
Warm over low heat until butter is melted.
Turn
into pie shell and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake on lower rack of oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until filling is set in center.
Cool before cutting.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Mix butter and Velveeta and melt (can use microwave) just enough to stir easily. Mix everything together, add vanilla. Pour out on cookie sheet with sides or 9x13 cake pan for thicker fudge. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: In 4-quart pan, cook the chicken in water until tender. Remove from pan.
Debone chicken and dice into small pieces. Return to pan.
Add celery, onion, corn and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until corn is tender.
Bring chicken broth to boiling and add noodles (as many or as few as you like).
Just before serving, stir in sliced eggs and heat for 5 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Grease pan (9 x 9-inch or muffin pan).
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan and let set for 15 minutes.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix together and serve with cut up, raw vegetables.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook beef and onions in small amount of water.
Drain all water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: tortillas and dip
directions: Eat with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs for 3 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken 'n' chips
directions: Take a chicken and pull off skin.
Put in square pan lined in aluminum foil.
Sprinkle garlic salt and lemon pepper over chicken.
Bake for 25 minutes on 400°.
Take out and turn over. Bake for another 25 minutes.
Take out and drain juice.
Coat with butter.
Cover completely with crushed chips.
Broil until chips are golden brown.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring the first two ingredients to a boil and cool to room temperature.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold or long casserole dish.
Stays congealed well.

title: florentine pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain. Add other vegetable ingredients except bacon, egg and spinach.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt Crisco, add water, salt and sugar and dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water and 1/4 teaspoon of sugar.
Beat eggs in large pot.
Add sugar, Crisco and warm water mixture.
Mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Then beat in flour until too stiff for beater.
Remove beaters and stir the rest of flour in.
Place dough in greased crock or Tupperware.
Cover and put in warm place to raise.
When double, punch down and let raise again.
Then make into rolls, any kind.

title: chop suey
directions: Fry meat (chop and drain).
Add Del Monte and 1 can of water for each.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste and Tabasco sauce. Let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Pour over ditalini or elbow macaroni. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Precook carrots a little.
Boil tomato soup, sugar and 1/4 can water for 1 minute.
Cut bacon into small pieces.
Mix carrots, soup and bacon together in lightly greased casserole.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour or until carrots are tender.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Let Grape-Nuts stand in warm milk for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add to milk mixture and bake pudding in pan of water in a slow oven.
Raisins or dates may be added.

title: german honey almond cake(serves 12)
directions: Reserve 48 whole almonds.
In blender or food processor, chop remaining almonds until finely ground.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy salad(serves six)
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Combine Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry Jell-O.
Add fruit cocktail.
Fold together well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Add egg; beat well. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread into foil-lined 9-inch square baking pan.

title: mexican bean dip(microwave)
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix into refried beans.
Spread into low roasting pan (9 x 12-inch).
Spread sour cream over bean mixture. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes until warm.
Garnish with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; combine in bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form stiff dough, beating after each addition.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Stir down; put into well-greased 8-inch round casserole (1 1/2 to 2-quarts).
Let rise until light, 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Place over bread.
Add other ingredients together except cheese.
Add to baking dish and then add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and cool.
Grind apple, orange and cranberries.
Add sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add to jello.
Add nuts.
Let jell and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Make a well in the flour mix and add oil, sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Toss macaroni with oil. Add all remaining ingredients. Pour into lightly greased crock pot. Stir well. Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: 4-step lemon lush
directions: Step 1:
Mix well margarine, flour and pecans, and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: appetizer loaf
directions: Shred or cream English cheese or Philadelphia creamed cheese. Mix it well with these ingredients:
onion, green pepper, olives, sour pickles, pimento, egg, cracker crumbs, salad dressing and salt.
Form into a roll; wrap in a wax paper.
Chill overnight. Place roll on lettuce leaves on appetizer tray with crackers. Garnish with stuffed olives.

title: great crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, except add 1/4 cup of the Cheddar cheese to mixture.
Place remaining 1/4 cup cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serve warm with crackers.
Makes a great hors d'oeuvre!

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Layer in dish:
onions, chicken, soup, tomatoes, chips and cheese.
Put a few chips on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy potatoes for a crowd
directions: The most difficult thing about this recipe is mixing it all together.
Put into a large casserole and crumble bacon on top. Do not use bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into large containers and freeze. Remove from freezer and thaw to slush stage.

title: syl's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, egg substitute and spices.
Add milk and blend.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: quick easy broccoli soup
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients just before boiling.

title: my mother's swedish spritz cookies
directions: Cream Parkay (must be Parkay) and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add sifted flour and work into smooth dough with hands.
When smooth, place in Spritz tube, using blade of your choice.
Cut or shape and place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
(I usually cut recipe in half.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend well. Add nuts.
Divide into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
(I check with toothpick.)
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: okra and tomato casserole
directions: Spray a casserole dish with Pam.
Place okra in bottom of dish, then add sliced pepper, sliced onion, tomatoes and Ro-Tel. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with pats of butter and sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, sprinkle with cheese on top and place back in oven until it is bubbly or melted.
Quick and easy and very good.

title: chicken and spinach calzones(makes 4 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spray medium nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken; cook and stir 5 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add onion and garlic; cook 1 to 2 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in pizza sauce and Romano cheese.
Remove from heat. Stir in spinach and Mozzarella cheese.
Remove pizza dough from can; do not unroll.
Cut roll into 4 equal portions.
Roll each portion into 6 to 7-inch round.
Spoon 1/4 of spinach mixture onto half of each round.
Fold untopped half over filling; press edges together.
Place on cookie sheet; reshape if necessary.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking pan. Cook beef and onions in a

title: easy tuna noodle dish
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions, except reduce the water to 3 cups total.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve.

title: children's daiquiri delight
directions: Put everything into a blender; process until smooth.
Serve.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar, cream, oleo and Karo syrup.
Cook until it forms a firm soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and vanilla; stir until it thickens.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; mix together and press onto bottom of pan.
Layer coconut, nuts, chocolate chips and marshmallows over crust.
Drizzle condensed milk evenly over all. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; drizzle with melted chocolate.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 32 squares.

title: red potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo. Add pretzels. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken to taste.
Place in greased baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dark bread
directions: Soak yeast and sugar for 15 minutes in water.
Add remaining ingredients and 2 cups white flour.
Beat 5 to 10 minutes with mixer.
Stir in rest of flour, enough to make a not too stiff bread dough.
Knead.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise and bake at 375° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: hoagie salad
directions: Dice onions small.
Dice tomatoes.
Cut salami, cheese and ham roughly in 1/4-inch squares.
Add all ingredients in a large bowl, then stir.
Add lettuce.
Add olive oil slowly.
Check to taste after 2nd tablespoon olive oil.
Spoon on sliced Italian or French bread.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use 2-quart glass pitcher bowl with handle.
Put peanuts, sugar, Karo and salt in bowl and cook in microwave 4 minutes. Remove and stir; return to microwave and cook 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in vanilla and oleo.
Return to microwave and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove and gently stir in the soda.
Stir until light and foamy; immediately pour onto foil-lined cookie sheet. Let cool for 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix Good Seasons, olive oil, water and vinegar together. Marinate chicken breasts, cut in half, for 1 hour or longer in dressing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle apples with 3/4 cup sugar mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Blend remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak lima beans overnight.
The next day, cook until beans are tender.
Drain and reserve approximately 1/2 condensed soup can of lima bean broth.
Put in baking dish and add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 2 hours in 350° oven, uncovered, for 15 minutes if runny.
If in a hurry, substitute 3 cans of lima beans for dry ones.

title: turkey divan
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Beat eggs in a separate bowl.
Mix sugar, eggs and cornstarch together; then add pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a smaller casserole dish.

title: veggie and shrimp bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange cooked vegetables on bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Layer shredded Cheddar on top of vegetables. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Romano. Layer shrimp, then sprinkle with remaining Romano. Beat the eggs with the wine, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and salt and pour over all. Spread the soup (undiluted) over the casserole and sprinkle with the bread crumbs. Bake for 1 hour.

title: dee's spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Cook spinach and squeeze out excess water.
Mix together all ingredients, reserving some Mozzarella for top.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish (lightly sprayed with cooking spray).
Sprinkle reserved Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with crackers or toast points.

title: glazed cinnamon raisin rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, oats and yeast. Heat milk, sugar, margarine and salt until warm (120°) and margarine is almost melted; stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture along with egg.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice for five minutes less than package directions.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a greased Pam casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: "crock-pot" chili
directions: *Ground turkey may be used.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add milk to soup until smooth.
Add tuna fish and corn or peas to soup, then add to noodles.
Blend well.
Top with chips or corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease pans.
Combine oats, wheat germ, bran and milk in large bowl.
In saucepan, heat honey and oil over medium heat until thin and runny.
Add only mixture to oat mixture; mix well.
Spread mix thin and even on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Spoon in large bowl.
Add raisins, chocolate chips, peanuts, coconut and sunflower seeds.

title: chocolate top cookies
directions: Roll into 24 balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press thumb in center.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Watch closely.
Will brown quickly at last.

title: turtles
directions: In double boiler, mix caramels and milk until creamy. Stir in pecans. Spoon onto greased wax paper in little mounds. Chill in refrigerator.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook separately the macaroni in boiling water.
In 1 tablespoon of butter, saute chopped onion in a skillet on low heat until tender.
Add tuna and softened cream cheese.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add cream soup. Mix.
Let simmer.

title: spaghetti roma
directions: Cook spaghetti per package directions; drain and keep warm. Heat oil and butter; add garlic, salt and oregano; cook 5 minutes. Sprinkle oil mixture, egg and parsley over spaghetti; toss and serve sprinkled with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: lettuce dressing
directions: Put ingredients into a jar and shake well.

title: dunken's delight dip
directions: Press spinach to remove water.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator until serving time.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Prepare broccoli according to box directions.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add cornbread mix, onion, eggs and sour cream to broccoli.
Mix well.
Mix 1 stick margarine in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse and drain in strainer the sauerkraut.
Heat to boiling the sugar, vinegar and oil.
Place sauerkraut in bowl.
Pour boiled mixture over it.
Add celery and green pepper.
Mix well together.
Chill overnight, covered.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, slowly saute potatoes in butter until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of butter in pan.
Add soup, cheese, garlic, milk, almonds and onions.
In baking dish, mix rice and broccoli, then add other mixture on top and mix in.
You may add ham, chicken or tuna.
Also may add green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook chopped onion and pepper in oil until tender and browned. Add meat and cook until well done.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt, tomato sauce and tomatoes; cook about 20 minutes. Add chili powder and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside and let cool; drain off fat and liquid from top of chili. Reheat when ready to be eaten alone, with beans or with hot dogs.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda, and salt. Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid to creamed mixture; add cherries and nuts. Bake in bread pan at 350 for one hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat the pineapple, including the juice, to boiling.
Add the jello.
Cool.
Add the buttermilk.
Chill until thick.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add water, salad dressing and vanilla. Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.
Great for chips or veggies.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all and bake in greased tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 70 minutes.
Divide juice (1 1/2 cups each) and place in tight container and give to a friend with a copy of the recipe as soon as possible.
Makes 6 starts (or 5).

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add rice and brown.
Add water, soup mix and soy sauce.
Cook until water evaporates.
Add eggs and heat until eggs are well done.

title: fruit drink
directions: Blend fruits and juice in blender until smooth. Add ice. Very good on hot summer days.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dough can be used for making cinnamon rolls.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours. Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill until set or overnight.
A favorite.

title: potatoes and cheese
directions: Put layer of potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Pour half of milk and soup over layer.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Use covered dish.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine apples, orange and walnuts in bowl.
Toss with mixture of Marshmallow Creme, mayonnaise and ginger.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Mix the cookies and melted margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and freeze.

Add the ice cream to the crust and freeze. Bring to a boil the sugar, vanilla, margarine, milk and chocolate and boil for 1 minute. Add to the ice cream and re-freeze. Add Cool Whip and toasted almonds.
You can freeze Cool Whip but it is better to add almonds just before serving.

title: pea salad
directions: In medium bowl, gently combine peas, celery, onion, and cheese.
Add mayonnaise and seasonings. Stir to combine.
Serve chilled.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Place zucchini in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half of seasonings.
Layer tomatoes and onion over zucchini.
Sprinkle with remaining seasonings.
Top with cheese; dot with butter. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add meat in chunks; brown and drain. Combine soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes; remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: May add any other vegetables if you like.
May also use tuna with dish instead of chicken.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil the sugar, water, vinegar and salt until the syrup reaches hard ball stage.
Add vanilla.
While mixture is still hot, pour over popcorn and mix well.
When cold enough to handle, grease hands with butter and shape into balls.

title: corn dressing
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peach pineapple dessert
directions: In a small bowl pace pineapple and peaches.
Sprinkle pudding over fruit and stir.
Place in an oblong pan and top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover and microwave at Medium power for 10 minutes. Stir well.	Remove bay leaf.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.
Use crushed ice in punch bowl to cool it.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (6 x 10-inch), melt butter in oven. Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well. Press on bottom of dish.

title: ham and cheese brunch
directions: Combine bread, ham, cheese and mushrooms.
Place 1/3 of mixture in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add beaten egg and mix thoroughly.
Gradually add water to make a thin batter.
Heat cooking oil in skillet.
Spoon batter in hot oil to make small cakes.
Fry until golden brown.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, baking powder and milk; beat well together.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (or until tests done).

title: chicken wings extraordinaire
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips.
Cut each wing in half and place in a shallow glass baking dish, side by side.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, preheat oven to 400° and bake the wings 40 to 45 minutes until well browned. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: dutch stew
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in a large pan.
Chop cabbage and add to beef mixture.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Good with cornbread!

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt butter and add flour, spices, ground beef, pepper and onion; saute until meat is brown.
Add ketchup, hot sauce and milk; add cheese and stir until melted.
Sprinkle with cumin, garlic salt, chili powder and fresh cilantro.
Serve with chips.

title: pie crust
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Add egg, vinegar and cold water.
Mix.
Roll out for pie crust.

title: orange bavarian dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of the orange juice and heat over hot water.
Combine remaining 1 1/4 cups orange juice with sugar.
Add gelatin and set in cold place, stirring occasionally to dissolve sugar.
When mixture is set to a soft jelly, whip the cream until stiff.
Fold in lemon juice and then orange gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and set.
Serves 8.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into loaf.
Place in shallow pan. Put in a preheated
350° oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Mix very well. Spoon into a serving dish.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter until a soft ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Beat egg yolks well.
After milk, sugar and butter is cooked, add melted chocolate.
Add beaten egg yolks and salt to hot mixture.
Beat until ready to spread.
Add vanilla and spread on layer cake.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into dish.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: green beans
directions: Combine ingredients, adding water to top of beans.
Cover. Cook beans until they are tender.
Remove the lid and dry all the water out, stirring often.

title: waffles(vafler)
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon-colored.
Add sugar gradually and beat until creamy.
Add sour cream and buttermilk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add flavoring and melted butter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in waffle maker until golden color.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1/4 cup brown sugar together.
Pat mixture into an 8 x 10-inch pan.

Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Combine eggs with rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spread over the baked pastry. Return to oven and bake 20 to 30 minutes. When cold, ice with powdered sugar icing. Sprinkle some chopped nuts over top and cut into bars of desired size when cooled well.

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until cookies are set but not brown. While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: scotcharoos
directions: In large pan, cook the white sugar and white Karo syrup until boils; remove.
Add the peanut butter and Rice Krispies cereal; mix all well.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In microwave or double boiler, melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips and spread on top of other mixture.

title: celery and apple salad
directions: Whisk first five ingredients.
Toss with celery and apple. Serves 2.

title: mother's no fail cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites in large bowl until stiff. Mix milk and vanilla together in another bowl and set both aside. Sift dry ingredients together, then add softened shortening.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Pour batter into stiff egg whites and fold in with slotted spoon; pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Top with favorite icing or just dust with powdered sugar.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Mix well and place in an oven-safe casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Top with can of chow mein noodles during the final 15 minutes of baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until done.
Drain and add cream of chicken soup and sour cream and mix.
Melt margarine and mix in bag of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Line casserole dish with 3/4 of stuffing mixture and then add vegetable mixture.
Top with the remaining stuffing mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover before cooking.

title: tomato grits
directions: Prep Time: 10 minutes.
Cook Time:
55 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry bread(or muffins)
directions: Beat egg and stir in sugar, oil and orange juice.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well, then stir in nuts and blueberries.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick tests done.

title: chili(baked)
directions: Brown bacon; drain and crumble.
Add onions and brown.
Add ground meat and brown.
Add seasonings.
Add kidney beans and tomatoes; mix.
Cover with cubes of bread.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Great with baked potato and salad.

title: company roast
directions: Rub roast with garlic salt then hickory salt, then Worcestershire sauce.
Pour large bottle of A.1. over roast and add 1 bottle water.
Add onion rings.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes per pound.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (will be stiff).
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to wire rack.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Put the rice in the boiling water.
Cook for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cook the chicken in some more water.
Use a separate pan.
Cut up the cooked chicken and add it to the rice.
Add salt, pepper and one pour of Tony's sauce.
Cook for 10 more minutes. Serve with rolls, mashed potatoes and gravy.
(No other vegetables!)

title: olympia pepper pot
directions: Firm oysters by boiling in salted water for 30 seconds. Drain.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Heat salted water in pan.
Add broccoli; cook until tender. Drain.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole. Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: texas barbecue sauce(crock-pot)
directions: Cook meat in crock-pot.
When almost done, combine all ingredients and cook in saucepan.
Combine sauce with meat in crock-pot; cook for 30 minutes.

title: stacki-uppi
directions: Place each of the ingredients in separate bowls, keeping in the order given.
Serve buffet style.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Note:
One 12 ounce package of chocolate chips may be substituted for peanut butter.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Fry onion and celery until done in 3 tablespoons of cooking oil.
Add soup, stir, add rice and broccoli and put into a casserole dish.
Cover top with grated cheese of choice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Have all the juices cold.
Combine juices.
Dissolve the powdered sugar in the lemon juice.
Add the ginger ale just before you serve it.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pot roast with natural gravy
directions: In a large heavy pot, add the oil and beef.
Brown meat on both sides.
Add water to cover meat.

Cook over medium heat until you can easily break meat apart with a fork, usually 4 to 5 hours. While cooking, watch the water and don't let it boil away until the meat starts to get tender, then let it boil down to where you have only 1 1/2 cups of broth left.
Keep it at this level until the meat is done.
When the meat is done, carefully remove it to a serving dish.
The remaining broth can be used as is or you can thicken it by mixing 1 tablespoon flour to 1/2 cup water and then add to the broth for a thicker gravy.

title: eggs, bread and cheese souffle
directions: Spread margarine on both sides of bread.
Place in alternate layers of cheese and bread, 2 layers each.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: brownie kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line miniature muffin pan with small paper baking cups (1 3/4-inch).

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Boil to hard-crack stage. Pour over popped corn. Make balls with buttered hands.

title: jody's easy cake
directions: Combine cake mix and butter.
Press into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.
After crust is cool, put cherry pie filling on top.
Layer with Cool Whip; drizzle chocolate syrup over the top.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and dash of salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Very slowly add sugar syrup to egg whites in mixing bowl.
Beat constantly with electric mixer until stiff peaks form, about 7 minutes.
Beat in vanilla.
Frosts tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers or one 10-inch tube cake.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook beets.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water and boil 5 minutes.
Add beets and let stand over low heat 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring to boiling point and add butter.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of peppers and remove seeds.
Cook peppers for 5 minutes and drain.

title: all-in-one-breakfast
directions: Saute first three ingredients in butter in skillet until brown. Add frozen shredded potatoes and cook until potatoes are done. Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs and salt.
Add to cooked sausage and cook until eggs are nearly set.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch casserole dish and add potato mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted, approximately 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: grandma's jonnie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: grilled parmesan spuds
directions: Place cast iron skillet on briquettes in gas grill or any grill.
Melt margarine in skillet on low setting.
Combine cheese, flour, peppers, & salt in bowl.
Dampen potato halves in water, place in dry mixture.
Put in cast iron skillet.
Cook on medium setting with grill cover down for 35 minutes or until done.
Turn once.

title: candy apple delight
directions: Mix all together, not too long before serving.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together for about 15 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Slowly add the flour and lemon extract. Now, fold in 7-Up.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: never fail yellow cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add one egg at a time, beating after each is added.
Mix in flour and milk.
Pour into greased cake pans and bake at 350° until sides leave pans. Makes 5 or 6 (12-inch) layers.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Layer in bottom of spring-form pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together except corn meal.
When well mixed, add corn meal.
Pour into greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baconetti
directions: Fry bacon and onion until tender, but not crisp.
Add tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook and drain capellini.

title: pumpkin-pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients first, then add all other except pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water to beef; simmer 10 minutes. Combine vegetables, cheese and beef in a large bowl.
Top with taco sauce.
Crumble taco shells (or tortilla chips) on top.

title: fruit dip
directions: In bowl beat cheese and butter until smooth.
Beat in marshmallow cream and fold in Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit. Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together except sour cream.
Place half in Pyrex dish and chill, then spread with sour cream and cover with remaining Jell-O mixture.
Chill.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, garlic, green pepper in butter until soft.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Serve with rice.

title: summer zucchini
directions: Slice squash, tomato and onion. Put into baking dish and cover with cheese. Bake at 350°, covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 more minutes.
Delicious!!!

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cap'n krisp clusters
directions: Melt almond bark.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Candy will harden in about 45 minutes. If mixture gets too stiff, reheat in microwave.

title: pecan chews
directions: Chop pecans finely.
If a grinder is used, put sugar along with the nuts.
If using blender, whirl for only a second, then put in sugar and blend together.
Fold the nut-sugar mixture into the stiffly beaten egg white and roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, allowing plenty of room between.
Press a half or quarter pecan on each.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Watch carefully, baking time depends on how finely the nuts are chopped.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Put oleo, flour and nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
(This will be your crust.)

title: mexican chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender, stirring constantly.
Add beans, tomatoes, broth, chilies, corn, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir to combine.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: beef baked beans
directions: Saute beef and onion in shortening until meat is brown; drain off excess fat.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to meat mixture.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine chicken broth, half and half, potato flakes, 3-1/2 cups cheese and pepper. Mix well and bring to a boil over medium-high heat and cook for 2-3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Top with the green onions and remaining cheese. Serve immediately.

title: lemon jello cheese cake
directions: Mix together with fork until well blended.
Line 9 x 13-inch or two small pans with mixture, reserving about 1/2 cup garnish.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Bring all liquids to a boil.
Add chicken.
Boil 1/2 hour longer.
Put everything in a large baking pan.
Bake 1/2 hour longer in 350° oven.

title: apple-cranberry relish
directions: Chop oranges, apples and cranberries in food processor into fine pieces.
Add sugar and mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator.
This relish gets better as it seasons.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use firm fruits as dippers. Refrigerate any leftover dip.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Dice in 1-inch pieces when cool.
Dice onion.
Add onion and cheese to potatoes.
Fry bacon and crumble; add to potatoes.
Add enough mayonnaise until it mixes well.

title: apple snowballs
directions: Soften ice cream; blend in brandy flavoring, apples and candied fruit. Freeze firm.
Shape into balls with ice cream scoop.
Roll in coconut.
Return to freezer until ready to serve. Serve with any favorite chocolate or fudge sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 snowballs.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Combine cheeses, lemon juice, garlic powder and red pepper.
Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in nuts.
Shape in a roll about 1 1/2-inches across.
Sprinkle roll with mixture of chili powder and paprika.
Chill several hours.
Before serving, let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: peach slush
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed.
Add peach daiquiri mix. Add Peach Schnapps.
Freeze.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: almond roca
directions: Cook butter and sugar to hard crack stage.

title: power house cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, soda and salt. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, beat butter with electric mixer 30 seconds. Beat in sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture. Beat until well combined. Stir in oatmeal, coconut, raisins, chocolate pieces and walnuts. Drop rounded teaspoonful 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are lightly browned. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing to cooling racks.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra, dry, slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix together flour, corn meal, salt and pepper.
Pour egg over okra and stir well.
Dredge in flour mixture.
Heat skillet; add oil and shortening.
Add okra and fry until brown.
Stir often to prevent burning.
Drain well before serving.

title: hatie's loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas egg dish(can make the night before)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease round casserole (9-inch approximately).
Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion in bottom.
Beat remaining ingredients 1 minute by hand mixer.
Pour into casserole.
Bake 45 minutes until a knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: crescent cream finger cookies
directions: Put 1 can of crescent rolls on greased jelly roll pan, using your fingers to smooth out on pan.
Pinch the seams together.
Mix well the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crescent roll layer. Take another can of crescent rolls and smooth out over the cream cheese.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over the crescent rolls.
Next, take the sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top. Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven in a pan no larger than 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inches.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients except peaches and mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Place drained peaches over mixture.

title: curry chicken and rice
directions: Brown onion and all spices in butter.
Add meat and brown. Add water to cover.
Simmer.
Cook rice.
Serve over rice.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put vanilla pudding in a bowl; add milk, flour, condensed milk, whipped cream and bananas.
Mix together with a large spoon.
Put in a pan and layer with vanilla wafers.

title: carrot dip
directions: Combine carrots, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, or until tender.
Stir after about 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1 tablespoon liquid.
Stir in green onions, sour cream, brown sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dill weed.
Reserve liquid.
Cover. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with blender. Set in fridge for 10 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and marshmallows in a mixing bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling and combine with the first mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla which have been beaten together first and mix well.
This will be a thin batter with some marshmallows floating on top.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add onion, garlic, beans, 2 cups water, tomatoes, sauce, oregano, chili powder and peppers to large pot.
Cook uncovered over low for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese over each serving.
Makes 8 servings, with 3 grams fat in each.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Melt butter and add the vinegar and brown sugar.
Heat only until well blended.
Add peach puree.
Heat again only enough to blend the mixture to a smooth sauce.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Cut down on the salt and use Mrs. Dash or Old Bay for flavor.
Grill chicken or bake in the oven until done.
Serve a portion of chicken and spoon peach sauce over it, or line a baking dish with heavy foil.
Place the chicken in the baking dish and broil for 10 minutes on each side.
After both sides have browned, baste with the peach sauce and allow to cook for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook for 5 minutes on the other side.
Baste chicken with more sauce and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat the butter in frying pan. Slice the onions and brown in butter until almost burned. Heat the consomm in another pan. Pour this over the onions and let boil slowly about 10 minutes. Brown Melba toast or French bread in butter. Put in the soup. Grate a lot of Swiss cheese and pour on top. Place under broiler until the cheese melts. Serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1/2 can tomato sauce; shape into loaf. Pour remaining tomato sauce over loaf and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and refrigerate until slightly firm, spreadable.
Spread on buns.
Add ham and cheese. Wrap in foil.
Heat in a 250° oven for 30 minutes.

title: buffet vegetables
directions: Mix beans, water chestnuts, bean sprouts and grated cheese. Add butter and bake at 300° for 20 minutes, until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Makes 8 servings, each with 143 calories, 8 grams of fat and 8 mg.
cholesterol.

title: lemon delight cake
directions: Mix together flour, nuts and butter; press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°; cool.
Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread on crust.
Beat together pudding, milk and lemon juice and spread on cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate for several hours or overnight; serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with pecans, pretzels and sugar.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in large mixer bowl.
Cut in butter with mixer at low speed.
Add mixture of milk, eggs and yeast; mix well.
Brush with melted butter.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Use to make Apple Kuchen, cinnamon rolls or pecan rolls.
Serves 16.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Beat in egg yolks, lemon juice and food coloring.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into baked pie crust.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours until firm.

title: chicken liver dip
directions: Cut chicken livers into small pieces.
Melt butter or margarine with garlic.
Saute livers until cooked through.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rum.
Cool.
Combine mixture in a blender with cream cheese, yogurt, salt and basil.
Blend until smooth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers and/or raw vegetables.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese.
Dip fruit of choice.

title: good dip
directions: Mix together and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cool and serve with crackers of your choice.

title: sesame chicken with honey dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients and set aside.
Mix crumbs and sesame seed.
Coat chicken with mayonnaise mixture, then crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot with Honey Dip.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix flour, nutmeg, salt
and
sugar.
Cut in margarine. Sprinkle with water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Roll out each pie as unrolled
dough gets tough.
Fill with dried apple or peach filling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool; cut into pieces. Line bottom and sides of punch bowl with the cake pieces. Mix pudding. Layer in punch bowl 3 bananas, 1 can strawberry filling, 1/2 of the pudding mix and 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Repeat layers, ending with
Cool Whip on top. Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry-banana freeze
directions: If desired, reserve 1 berry (sliced) and 4 thin banana slices, brushed with lemon juice, for garnish.
Set aside.
Cut remaining bananas into chunks; wrap in plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.

title: wilma taylor's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients; dot margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2-quart casserole.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Mix apricots and mustard and spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°. Baste and bake 10 more minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: At high heat in pan sprayed with nonstick spray or wok add chicken and stir 2 or 3 minutes or until cooked.
Stir in vegetables and cook 2 or 3 minutes; then add soy sauce, ginger, garlic, brown sugar and cooking wine.
Stir to blend.
Pour in the 2 tablespoons cornstarch and water.
Reduce heat to simmer until the sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Serve with steamed rice or fried rice.

title: peach punch
directions: Boil 2 cups of water to dissolve jello.
Freeze all.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons without ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add 1 bottle ginger ale.
Peach sherbet can be added.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in a deep saucepan until sizzling.
Add oysters and liquid.
Reduce flame and cook slowly approximately 3 to 5 minutes or until edges of oysters curl slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and heat quickly, but do not boil.
Serve immediately. Top with paprika and lumps of butter.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Cook sausage, onions and celery in a skillet over medium heat until sausage is browned and onion and celery are tender; drain. Place in a large bowl; add remaining ingredients, except celery leaves, stirring well.
Spoon dressing into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef until crumbly.
Stir in dry taco seasoning mix. Add tomatoes and corn.
Bring to a soft boil, stirring frequently.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, ginger and garlic.
Add tofu.
Toss lightly.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove tofu from soy mixture with a slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towel.
Stir cornstarch and water into soy mixture; set aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add celery, zucchini and bell pepper.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir in reserved soy mixture. Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Add tofu and tomato. Heat through and serve immediately.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper together. Set aside.
In a large cooker, add salt, tomato juice, chili sauce and beans. Bring to a boil. Add chili powder. Boil for 2 minutes, then add hamburger mixture. Boil for 30 minutes.

title: family reunion meatballs
directions: Make meatballs using Worcestershire sauce, ground beef, oatmeal and onion powder and salt.
Fry or bake meatballs until done (set to the side).

title: country cheese ball
directions: Finely chop cooked ham.
