Combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, 1/4 cup ham, minced onion and Worcestershire sauce; mix well. Shape into ball; coat with remaining ham.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grate cookies, set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter together.
Mix vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk and add to mixture, fold in Cool Whip.
Layer grated cookies alternately with mixture ending up with cookies on top.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Shred like amounts of american and velvets cheese. Add 1 tsp. sweet pickle relish, pimentos
and 1 Tbsp. sugar. Mix with enough Miracle whip to make it moist and creamy. Chill.

title: oriental marinated beef
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in jar and shake.
Pour over thinly sliced rare roast beef, tomatoes, sliced mushrooms, drained water chestnuts, green pepper (julienned) and scallions, chopped.
You can marinate meat, alone, overnight.
Then mix remaining vegetables or just mix all and serve over lettuce leaf platter.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: hershey's deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inch or rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain, about 3 cups.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs.
Form a pie crust; add spaghetti in a 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over this.
Pour spaghetti sauce on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart glass dish. Cook on Full power for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts, vanilla and margarine.
Cook 5 minutes on Full power.
Add baking soda.
Pour onto greased baking sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: slaw
directions: Shred first four ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
The longer it sits the better it is.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, sugar, mustard, salt and cayenne in the top of a double boiler.
Gradually stir in the milk.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat together cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Beat in butter and vanilla; pour into two butter flavored ready crust pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chocolate chips may be used also.
One teaspoon lemon juice added to regular cheese can be used.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: First mix fresh strawberries with 1/4 cup of sugar to form juice.
Then mix everything together at one time except eggs.Then mix eggs with mix, one at a time; mix well.
Pour in one 9 x 13-inch pan or a tube pan.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely before icing.

title: aunt minnie's hand lotion
directions: Place in the largest mixing bowl that you have.
Mix on low speed until thick and creamy.
If desired, add a few drops perfume.
If you want color, add a few drops food coloring.

title: green bean casserole, i
directions: Pour soup over beans.
Add other ingredients.
Stir and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chicken breasts with chipped beef
directions: Put 1 slice or two of beef on each chicken breast and wrap in bacon strips.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° covered for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until 3/4 done; cool.
Mix canned ingredients together.
Brown chopped onions in margarine.
Add to mixture. Grease casserole and put noodles in.
Pour mixture into noodles and mix.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar has dissolved.
Cool.
Add juices, pineapple and ginger ale.
Mix all together and freeze in ice trays.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Lightly cook and drain zucchini. Mix stuffing with margarine, saving 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix all ingredients with dressing (stuffing) mixture. Put in casserole and top with the 1/2 cup reserved stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my pantry clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Stir in garlic. Add other ingredients. Using soup can, add clam juice and fill with milk. Heat on low long enough to blend flavors. Do not boil.

title: carrot cake
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
In a large bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and mix well.
Stir in coconut, shredded carrot, pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until center of cake is firm to touch.
Cool in pan.
Frost as desired.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
In crock-pot, add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Allow to simmer in crock-pot until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs; gradually beat in sugar, then oil. Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, coarsely chopped nuts and vanilla. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake on lowest rack in oven 55 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes to cool before removing from pans.
(I like to make this into muffins.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Just cut up everything and put into bowl and stir well. Serve.

title: banana smoothie(kindergarten recipe)
directions: Take the peel off the banana. Put it in the blender.
Push the high button.
Add the ice cream and the ice cubes.
Push the high button again.
Pour the smoothie into a long glass.
Makes one yummy drink.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Slice apples into uncooked pie crust.
Pour mixture over apples.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Apples may be sprinkled with one package Sweet 'N Low if desired.

title: herbed broccoli salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, basil, garlic powder and black pepper; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, bring 2 inches salted water to a boil.
Add carrots and medallions; simmer 2 minutes. Add broccoli florets; simmer 1 minute.
Drain and place in a bowl; toss with reserved dressing.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled or overnight.
Serve garnished with lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: crescent roll cheesecake
directions: Lay the first package of crescent rolls out in 13 x 9 pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Boil for 1 minute (no more).
Then add peanut butter.
Stir in vanilla and then add oatmeal.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper; let harden. Will be hard in about 1 hour.

title: cucumber mint salad
directions: Using a whisk, combine the last 7 ingredients.
Allow this dressing to sit for 1 hour.
Now stir in your cucumbers and allow flavors to combine for 3 hours.
Divide evenly and serve cucumber salad on bibb lettuce.

title: hot rum drink("a holiday favorite")
directions: Cream the butter with sugar. Sprinkle the cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves over the sugar mixture and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate in covered container to store.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower, remove leaves and cut out core.
Cook, covered, in boiling, salted water for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Place cauliflower in a shallow ungreased baking pan.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread over cauliflower. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika; garnish with tomato wedges, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed (do not overcook).
Drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese with 1 stick of butter.
Add to drained broccoli. Put mixture into a rectangular greased glass dish.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with 1 stick melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes to heat thoroughly.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and mix. Add flour; mix. Blend in pecans and dates. Roll teaspoonful of dough into balls. Refrigerate balls for 1 to 2 hours. Bake on greased cookie sheet for about 20 minutes. Remove from oven and roll balls in powdered sugar. Sprinkle them again with powdered sugar when cool.

title: maudie's green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in juice until most of juice is out and beans are tender, then drain.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add sour cream, soup and cheese.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers or canned onion rings.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: chocolate-banana cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add cold milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture comes to a boil.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Remove to a bowl; cover surface with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until cool, about 1 hour.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Line baking dish with crustless cheese sandwiches.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over sandwiches.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: creamy giblet gravy
directions: Brown giblets and cook celery in butter until tender.
Blend in remaining ingredients; heat and stir.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine margarine and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill.
Combine brown sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 24 balls; press into miniature muffin pans.
Fill each cup 3/4 full of sugar/nut mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch (lightly greased) pan: potatoes, onion, sausage and cheese. Pour egg and milk mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy and yummy chocolate cake
directions: Add boiling water to cocoa and stir until smooth.
Cool. Measure and sift together into mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add in order, cooking oil, egg yolks, cooled cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.

title: easy drop rolls
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add all other ingredients and stir until blended.
Dough will be soft and sticky.
Place in airtight covered container and store in refrigerator several hours before using.
To serve, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: italian hot sauce
directions: Brown onions in olive oil. Add mushrooms. Add cut up Ortega peppers and simmer.
Next, add salt to taste and one large can tomato paste. Simmer slowly about 1 hour. Makes a large batch and freezes well.
Very hot.

title: opal's salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve over fresh tossed salad.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine sour cream, pudding and pineapple in a large bowl. Reserve some pineapple for garnish.
Mix well.
Pour into crusts. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix in large mixing bowl.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or more.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: disappearing chocolate cake
directions: Generously grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy; blend in eggs. Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder, soda and salt in bowl.
Add alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well.
Pour into pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Frost with Marshmallow Icing when cool.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets, then peel and slice thinly.
Fry bacon in skillet and drain. Saute onion in bacon fat until brown. Add dry ingredients, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Add water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in potatoes and bacon (crumbled in small bits).
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french toast
directions: In a bowl, lightly whip together egg substitute and milk. Place mixture in a shallow dish.
Dip bread slices, one at a time, into mixture.
Place on a baking tray that has been greased with some type of butter flavored baking spray or butter flavored Crisco.
Bake at 350° until bread is golden brown.
You may also fry over medium heat until a golden brown, if preferred.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Combine all but the cheese.
Put in greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 more minutes.

title: june's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt jelly in kettle.
Add ketchup and diced onion.

title: crunchy granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except cinnamon, in the order given.
Mix well with a spoon.

title: salsa
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water to remove skins.
Core and chop tomatoes into a large saucepan.
Combine all the ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or to desired thickness.
Immediately fill hot pint jars with salsa and leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Make sure all air bubbles are out of jars.
Wipe jar tops, put on hot lids and seal. Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large baking dish, combine beans, sugars and barbecue sauce.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain and add to bean mixture.
Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Stir in soups and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add cheese and Pet milk.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
For creamier dip, add more sour cream.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon 2 inches apart. Bake 12 minutes at 400°.

title: beer rolls
directions: Stir in all of your ingredients.
Grease and flour muffin pans. Bake at 350 degrees for about 10 to 20 minutes.

title: champion chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: asian slaw
directions: Remove packet from soup and set aside. Crush noodles. Place noodles in bottom of large bowl. Top with slaw mix. Sprinkle with almonds, sunflower seeds and green onions. Whisk together contents from flavor packet, sugar, oil and vinegar. Pour over slaw. Cover and chill 24 hours. Toss before serving. Serves 8 to 19.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Cool. Mix cream cheese until fluffy. Add milk and pudding mix. Then mix together and pour over cake. Next, spread the pineapple over cake. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Top with coconut.

title: fresh banana nut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box, decreasing water to 1/2 cup and adding 1 1/2 cups mashed bananas.
Add 3 tablespoons margarine, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 teaspoons sugar, salt and 1 more egg if mix only called for 1.
Stir 1 cup chopped nuts in last. Beat all ingredients until fluffy.
Pour into buttered pan and bake as suggested.

title: cranberry apple mold
directions: Sprinkle
gelatin
over cold water in a small saucepan; let stand
minutes.	Stir
over
low
heat
until liquid is almost boiling
and
gelatin is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat. Stir
in
cranberry
sauce and lemon juice.
Chill until the mixture
mounds when dropped from a spoon.	Fold in apple, celery and
nuts.	Turn
into a 3 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm; unmold and garnish with thinly sliced apples.

title: yogurt ranch dressing
directions: Whisk all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: cinnamon petals
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once, stir only until dough follows fork around.
Turn out on lightly floured surface. Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll in a 16 x 12-inch rectangle, 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with butter.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil and cut potatoes.
Add celery, salt, pepper and scallions.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add to potatoes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute sliced zucchini in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Saute garlic (3 cloves), 3 to 5 minutes and add tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes and then boil 10 to 12 minutes to thicken.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Squeeze juice out of kraut.
Add all ingredients to kraut. Mix well.
Let stand 24 to 48 hours (must).
Keeps indefinitely.

title: smoked ham slices and apple ham slices
directions: Put ham slices and apple rings in large dish; sprinkle with allspice.
Arrange ham slices on top of apples and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with plastic cling, microwave for 5 minutes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Slice bananas.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Keep refrigerated.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together
first
four
ingredients with your hands. Form into small	balls.	Place
on waxed paper and refrigerate to harden.
In microwave, melt chips and shortening.
Put in a small bowl for
dipping.	Take
toothpick and stick into ball. Dip ball 3/4
way
into
chocolate.	Put
back
on
wax
paper without letting
the sides touch.
Refrigerate until chocolate is hardened.
Smooth hole from toothpick with finger tip.

title: green beans for company
directions: Cook green beans until soft; drain.
Mix the soup, milk, soy sauce and 1/2 can onions with green beans.
Pour into casserole bowl and sprinkle remainder of onion on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Freeze.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Can also be frozen before they are baked.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in baked pie shell and chill.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water; mix into the softened cream cheese.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, grapes, pineapple, and nuts, tossing to blend. Blend in mayonnaise. Refrigerate until serving. Serve as sandwich spread or on bed of lettuce. Makes 20 servings.

title: imperial crab
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread the 2 tablespoons of eggs and 1 tablespoon water over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushrooms in sour cream sauce
directions: Saute half of the mushrooms in a third of the butter.
Remove with slotted spoon to a plate.
Repeat with remaining half of mushrooms and another third of butter.
Reserve excess liquid. Melt remaining butter in a saucepan.
Add garlic and saute until golden, but not browned.
Stir in flour.
Cook until bubbly.
Add broth, salt, pepper, dill weed, lemon and apple juices and excess liquid from cooking mushrooms.
Cook, stirring until sauce thickens.
At this point the sauce and mushrooms can be refrigerated separately until an hour before serving.
Reheat sauce before proceeding.
Empty sour cream into a medium bowl.
Gradually add heated sauce, stirring constantly.
Return to pan and fold in mushrooms.
Heat through and serve immediately from chafing dish.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute (mixture will be thick). Gently stir in 3 1/2 cups of the whipping topping. Spread into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Store leftover pie in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: irish brown soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix, but do not sift, the
white flour together with the whole-wheat flour.
Cut margarine into small pieces and rub into the combined flour until it resembles bread crumbs.
Add in and mix all other dry ingredients (including golden raisins), except the further tablespoon of white flour mentioned for kneading.
Slowly add buttermilk to the mixture with gentle mixing until it becomes a soft dough (about 2 cups of buttermilk will be needed).

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: 1. Beat oil, sugars, beef seasoning (from noodles) and vinegar in double boiler. Let cool.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef in oil; drain.
Add water, onion, carrots, potatoes and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in peas.
Bring to a boil.
Combine flour and water in a small bowl; stir until smooth.
Add to beef mixture. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: nappa chinese cabbage salad
directions: Melt oleo in a pan and saute sesame seed, noodles and almonds until light brown.
Cool and toss with cabbage and onions.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: *May substitute strawberry or blueberry pie filling for the cherry pie filling.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand for 1 to 2 hours.
Take the Jell-O and add boiling water.
Mix.
Let stand until rubbery. Then whip with beater until foamy.
Mix with cranberry mixture. Whip the whipping cream and fold in.
Put in mold or bowl.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour evenly into pie plate.
Bake until top is golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with tomato slices and bacon strips if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean stuff
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook bacon and cut up.
Drain fat from both meats.
Gently mix all together and bake uncovered in a very large dish or iron pot at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Good with ham and cornbread.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Blend together thoroughly eggs, salt, extracts, and Eagle Brand milk.
Add slowly 1 qt milk, then fold in whipped cream. Add nutmeg to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove and dice chicken.
In broth of chicken, add the 4 cans of soup and milk.
Put diced chicken in, then quarter the biscuits and drop them in, one at a time.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: fiesta chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans, onions, chili powder, bouillon granules, and cumin.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the corn and chilies to the pot.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, or until the flavors are well blended. Serve hot, topping each serving with cheese.
You may substitute ground turkey and fat-free cheese.

title: church windows candy
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients until just melted.
Add chopped nuts and colored marshmallows. Mix well.
Divide in half on foil that has been sprinkled with chopped nuts or coconut and shape into a roll and refrigerate.
Then slice.

title: peppery oven stew beef
directions: Use lean stew beef cut in cubes.
Coat in seasoned batter. Brown in oil on top of stove.
Pour off grease.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour.
Brown in oil to make gravy.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Pour into covered casserole dish or covered pan.
Place in oven at 350°.
Cook until almost done, then add bell pepper and onion. Cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: aunt mary's cold broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli to desired size, only using flower head. Crumble bacon into bowl.
Add mayonnaise to taste.
Add sugar to taste.
Add grated cheese, onion and red wine vinegar.
Mix these ingredients together, then add broccoli.
Mix all together well. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll in pecans.
Serve on crackers or celery.

title: spinach filled manicotti
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
Cut drained noodles in half widthwise.
Cook and drain spinach.
Shred Mozzarella cheese.
Mix the cheeses, spinach, spices and egg (optional).
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of mixture in the middle of each noodle and roll up.
Layer the dish with tomato sauce, roll-up, tomato sauce and more Mozzarella cheese (optional).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set 5 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Add eggs and Cool Whip to cake mix.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on Pam coated cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended; refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: microwave cracker jacks
directions: Place corn (and peanuts) in large, brown grocery bag*.
Combine brown sugars, margarine, syrup and salt in 2-quart glass bowl or measuring cup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring after every minute.
Then microwave additional 2 minutes on High.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour syrup mixture over popped corn.
Close bag and shake well.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Shake good and cook 1 more minute.
Pour into Pam-sprayed roaster.
Stir and cool.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add onions and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add potatoes and water. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream; gradually add milk.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Heat to serving temperature. Do not boil.
Makes 7 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Combine in a large bowl the remaining ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes. Add sifted mixture and beat for 1 minute.
Drop by teaspoon or roll into balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork to crisscross (flour fork). Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Makes approximately 2 to 3 dozen large cookies.

title: debbie's lazy way spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet or saucepan.
If onion is used, chop onion and cook with hamburger meat.
(It is not necessary to drain grease.)
Add tomato sauce, water and garlic salt.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti; cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally (1 to 2 times), or until liquid is cooked down.
Salt with garlic to taste, then serve.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Blend together for about 1 minute and serve.
